animal.description:
Please welcome Roxie to rescue!  She is a 7 year old sweetheart but is being surrendered because she and the younger resident female dog are not getting along.  Roxie has had several litters of pups and is currently living with a daughter from a 2018 litter.

Roxie likes children who know how to respect a dog's space, other dogs and people.  She has never been exposed to cats.  Roxie is a playful girl and enjoys naps in the sun, walks, water and riding in the car.  She is house broken, crate trained and knows how to use a doggy door.  Roxie is not a big fan of fireworks, thunder, gunshots, and any other extremely loud noise.  

An adoption fee of $150 applies.

Dog name and description:

 You must contact the  Westfield Animal Shelter  .  413.564.3129  This is a COURTESY POSTING. We DO NOT have this dog .

Luna is a Pyrenees mix. She is about a year and three months old.
She has been spay, vaccinated, blood tested and microchipped.
She is very sweet goofy girl.
She is affectionate, but not needy.
She is a huge alarm barker! If she hears something, she barks, a lot!
She is fearful of strangers but warms up after 10-15 minutes.
When she is worried, she get close by your side. She is insecure.
She is super playful.
She knows a few commands
She doesn't seem to be a fan of cats.
She is very dog selective.

She is at the Westfield Animal Shelter. Please contact them directly at
413.564.3129.   THIS IS A COURTESY POSTING  .

animal.description:
Super sweet and kind. He was found wandering a cemetery and no one came to claim him. He gets along with everybody and every dog. He would love a warm quiet house with a loving family to call home.
Age: Born 11/28/12
Weight:  50 pounds full grown guess
Energy Level: senior
Adoption fee: $295

Applications are at: www.rescuepups.org

Look for directions at: 
facebook.com/rescuepup585

Located in Friendship, NY approximately 90 minutes south from both Buffalo and Rochester. Rescue Pups works tirelessly to ensure that our dogs are well taken care of and they get the very best home that is a perfect match for them. While waiting to get adopted dogs are loved like family.Quality of care is the highest of our priorities. We hike daily, make sure everyone gets plenty of play time, a good quality diet and we try to do basic training. All our dogs are vaccinated, spayed or neutered, microchipped, and are given monthly advantage. The same person provides consistent quality of care.  Families who adopt from us get a well-balanced pet who trusts people. When you support us, your gift can help more dogs get adopted into loving homes. Together we can make a difference.

animal.description:
Is it a mouse or is it Artie!  Artie is a little 2-3lb four month old pomchi who is active, silly, and zips around like he is turbo charged.  He enjoys going bye bye and being tucked in my jacket as I work.  He sleeps on my pillow or under my chin.  He loves other little dogs and is likely too much for a senior pet to deal with He is fine with cats. I don’t usually pee pad train the dogs however he is so little that I cheated this time!  He can be a bit of a drama queen (whines) if he wants down and you don’t read his mind and help him at once.  He’s a dreamboat!
His forever home requirements are: 
No small children
Another friendly small dog 
Someone home most of the time
Graceful movers so not to step on him 
Impeccable vet reference 
I have not crated him 
No apartments please 
He is neutered vaccinated dewormed flea treated and chipped.  
If you have never applied to adopt we ask that you make a $25 nonrefundable donation that helps care for the animals.  Although we try, everyone  may not hear back from us.  We are not first come first serve.  We choose the best home for each dog. 
PayPal.me/spayitforward
Copy and paste for application if you have what he needs https://forms.gle/i6vCT6447Eew8NCg9

Charlie is about 11 months old.  She just came into rescue and needs to be vetted and spayed.  She is in a foster home with dogs and cats.  She is shy at first but warms up for attention. She is good with kids.

It will be a couple of weeks before she is ready for a new home.



THIS  IS NOT A WORKING DOG AND WILL NOT BE PLACED AS ONE. IT WOULD BREAK THE DOG'S HEART.


THE APPLICATION PROCESS CAN BE FOUND ON OUR WEBSITE AT
http://www.nepyresq.org/page/adoption-process-47.html.OUR DOGS ARE IN FOSTER HOMES ACROSS THE NORHTEAST. AFTER YOU ARE APPROVED YOU WILL BE GIVEN THE CONTACT INFORMATION FOR THE FOSTERS SO YOU CAN GO MEET THE DOG (S) .

YOU CAN NOT TRAIN A PYRENEES TO STAY IN YOUR YARD WITHOUT A FENCE. IT IS IN THIER NATURE. IF YOU WANT A DOG TO WALK OFF LEASH WITH YOU THIS IS NOT THE BREED FOR YOU.

The adoption fee is $400 due to cost of medical needs of our dogs. $450 for Dogs 12 months and under. You will receive a copy of their medical records when you adopt.

We DO NOT accept INVISIBLE fencing for the following reasons:
1) Most Pyrs ignore the pain and go through it.
2) This is a guardian breed and this fencing does not keep people or other animals out of your yard. The Pyr could take them as a threat or be attacked by them.

Most of these dogs are not a dog park breed. They bark a lot and can bother your neighbors.

animal.description:
Daisy is a beautiful 3-year-old German shepherd. She was taken to an Alabama shelter as a stray & never reclaimed by her owner. 

Daisy is a very sweet & friendly girl! She plays well with other dogs & really loves being outdoors! Daisy loves attention & affection. She's a very smart girl & would be very easy to train. Daisy does need to eat out of a slow feeder because she eats her food very quickly. She needs a little bit of work taking treats gently as she gets very excited. We believe she'd do best in a home with children ages 8 & up due to this. 

Daisy hasn't always had the best life before coming to rescue. She obviously wasn't fed enough & is currently gaining some weight. Sadly, Daisy is heartworm positive, but she will be treated prior to adoption. 

Daisy is such a wonderful dog & will make an excellent family companion! 

COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! IF you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application! Please email for an Application or copy and paste the following URL: 

https://fs26.formsite.com/nogreaterlove/form2/index.html 

Upon receipt of your application, the rescuer and foster in AL will contact you so you can ask any specific questions you may have! If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement! 

 Adoption Donation: Unless otherwise stated in the pet's bio, our standard adoption fee is $395 which covers age appropriate vaccines (DHPP vax) and (Rabies vax if 12 weeks and older), utd on flea/tick prevention and heartworm prevention, worming, heartworm test @ age 6 months or older, microchip, fostering costs and health certificate.

Thank you for your understanding and consideration and for helping the dogs and puppies in need!

We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21

PLEASE COMPLETE OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AT WWW.LOVEBUGSRESCUE.ORG IF YOU'D LIKE TO BE CONSIDERED FOR ADOPTION:

Chelsea is a darling 2 year old 13 lb Jack Russell mix with the cutest underbite. She found herself in the scary shelter without an owner in sight. Thankfully, she is now a Lovebug! Chelsea is a fun packed pooch who loves everyone she meets. She gets along well with other dogs, and can be quite playful.  She is also equally affectionate and loves her people. 

Chelsea walks well on leash and enjoys greeting everyone along the way. She is very smart and food motivated making training a breeze. She has already mastered default sit! Chelsea would do great with a family who enjoys taking their dog on adventures with them. She would do best in a home with a yard, and with a family who is home a more often than not. She is going to make an amazing addition to a very lucky family! 

Chelsea's adoption fee is $350 and that includes her spay, registered microchip, vaccines current, deworming and flea treatment. Apply to meet her at www.lovebugsrescue.org

Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)

animal.description:
Bo is an unapologetically big beautiful all happy all the time kinda lab!! Let's just say if you like a funny, happy, frisbee loving lab, then Bo is your fella!
Bo came into GDR weighing close to 130pds and we have been slowly whittling him down to a healthier weight so he can run and play and enjoy life like he really wants to. He has been great with all the dogs and humans and cats he meets, he is learning better leash manners which his previous person admitted she never taught him, and he is just an all around good ol' boy. 
Bo is 8YO and in great health with the usual bumps that grow on big dogs as they age, but since they are fatty and cancer free, they don't need to be removed. Besides his weight and cute piggly wiggly ears, he's just perfect!!
If you enjoy the company of a  great older lab whose main goal is to enjoy life and bring a little comic relief into yours, then come meet Bo!

We kindly ask that you contact us thru Petfinder or Laura@GreatDawgRescue.org for each dawgs adoption status. We will then follow up with a phone interview and if applicable, send home an Adoption Application.  As always, a Home Visit with you and your family and a Vet Reference will be done prior to placing any of our dawgs to ensure the best match for each dawgs needs. Much thanks!!
https://GreatDawgRescue.org

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.Sweet Skye was bred as a lab animal and only knew a cage as her whole world. That cage represented pain and fear. She was rescued after years of torture and went to live in a real home where she was loved and she has learned that people can be good and beds can be soft. She knows now what grass under her feet feels like and how wonderful it is to stretch her legs and run in her yard. Play is at long last something she has discovered. Life was finally going well for Skye. And then her family fell apart. Of course we have stepped in to help her find a new place where she will be loved and cared for. A place once again with a soft bed and a fenced yard where she can safely play. NO CRATES! She is terrified of crates, and for good reason! She has shown herself fine with other dogs, cats, and kids. Her foster says ' She needs someone to be attentive to her needs and take her out frequently so she can go to the bathroom like a good girl. She sleeps a lot but still has lots of energy for the kids. She does not bark or howl surprisingly. I have heard her bark only 3 times.' She needs a safe, loving place where her naturally sweet temperament will be valued. Is it possible that you will be her angel?
Note from her foster: Being a beagle, Skye is going to need a yard with a physical fence where she can run and play safely.
If you are interested in Skye, please fill out an application at:
https://reachoutrescue.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=4588 Or contact:
rorrcanine@gmail.com

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Jenny Cope (giveadogahome@live.com) for more information about this pet.
Be sure to read ALL information provided.

CAM was saved from a high kill shelter in Texas where dogs often have only 3 days to be saved. CAM is neutered, rabies, core vaccines, heartworm/tick disease tested negative for all. He is de-wormed, monthly preventatives and microchipped. At the time of rescue at the end of November 2020, he weighed around 50 pounds and has an estimated date of birth 9 May 2019. We cannot say for sure what breed he is, so we expect families to do their own research on his look and size and decide what breed you think he is and if you have the lifestyle suitable for his needs.

More pictures and possible video's can be found on his page on the rescue website.

CAM has been at the rescue since November 2020 and unbelievably has had little interest from anyone. He is a sweet boy, a nice size, gets on good with other dogs here at the rescue, living in a communal area where he shares his food, water, several beds and hang out areas and has access to a large fenced in area where he will explore, or chase and play with the other dogs.

We do not know any history on why CAM ended up in the kill shelter, he has always been mild mannered whilst here, he is a good communicator and will let you know by his body language or a low growl if he is not happy with something - just normal ways that dogs communicate and all pet owners should ensure they are familiar and understand dogs body language on how they communicate.

CAM would love an active family who goes on walks, hikes, runs, trips to the beach or lake where he can explore and live an all round happy, full, healthy life.

We are not able to say how he will be around cats or livestock.

All dogs use dog doors to go out and do their business or to enjoy the cool, fresh weather in their dog runs or communal areas. We cannot say if a dog is house-trained, however, we expect families to understand that all dogs need a transition period and accidents could happen and training is most definitely needed.

All dogs are fed Rachael Ray Nutrish PEAK Natural Dry Dog Food, Grain Free Western Grasslands Recipe with Bison. Rachael Ray Nutrish Peak Dog Food receives the Dog Food Advisor's second-highest tier rating of 4.5 stars.

CAM is available for adoption for an adoption fee of $350

This fee is not negotiable and is used to cover the rescue costs of pulling, vetting, health certificate, transport from Texas to Maine, monthly preventatives, supplements, food, general day to day cost of running a brick and mortar rescue and anything else that is needed. Canadian adopters need to know that customs charge 15% taxes when entering into Canada.

Due to borders being closed, it is up to families to call the US and Canadian borders to find the current details on border crossing. Animal Welfare is deemed essential in the US, but quarantine rules entering back into Canada must be followed.

If you feel that you have the heart and home to give this precious soul a wonderful life, please go to our website, under the ADOPTION INFO tab, complete, then submit the APPLICATION. Our process takes around 2-4 days, and ensuring your references are aware that we will be calling, could speed up the process. Once you have been approved, we discuss any questions in regards to the dog you are wanting to adopt, then you complete and submit the contract, make payment and then we can work out the pick up / transport arrangements.

Please do NOT submit an application if you are not looking to take home a new best friend within the next few weeks.

https://www.giveadogahome-sanantonio.org/forms/form?formid=5838

ALL Dogs are LOCATED AT THE RESCUE IN SEBEC, MAINE. We post in various states along the east coast and Canada where we have had lots of successful adoptions to enable more exposure for these beautiful saved souls. Families will need to be prepared to travel to the rescue to meet and take home their new best friend. Sebec is located just outside the towns of Dover-Foxcroft and Milo (approx 8 miles) and approx 45 miles from Bangor. There are also lots of hotels, motels, pet friendly accommodations and wonderful camp-sites for the more adventurous families and what a great way to get to know your new best friend.

Click here to watch a video of CAM - $350.

animal.description:
SIMBA ~2 years old. Good with dogs & Older Considerate Kids. Cats TBD. Needs companion animal
GSRA adopts to residents of VA, NC, and SC only
Have you ever heard the saying that dogs don't live in the past? Well, this sweet boy Simba is a prime example of one that has left his past behind him. You see, Simba was tied out on a tether and neglected to the point that he developed an embedded collar. Thankfully animal control was finally alerted and came to his rescue. He was able to receive the surgery he so desperately needed and now, after months of treatment, is all healed up. Because of this, he CANNOT have a collar or anything tight around his neck ever again. He also hates to be picked up but will easily jump in the car, etc. Even after what he went through, this boy has nothing but LOVE to give.
Simba is a sweet little guy who loves life. He might be a little shy when he first meets you but if you give him a little time, he is a total lovebug. He loves going for walks, hikes in the woods, rides well in the car and LOVES playing with his toys. He loves attention and will rub up against you like a cat to get a little pet or two. He gets along great with my pup and did well on a cat test done at the shelter but we would retest just to be sure. Simba has free reign 24/7 along with my pup and I haven't had any issues. Simba has moderate energy and would best with a companion to play with. But he also knows how to settle down when he needs to.
Simba would love a family who has a fenced yard and another dog that he can run and play with. He will need someone who is willing to work with him on training. He seems to pick up on things pretty well but will need some work. He is treat motivated so that is a huge plus. He does jump when excited and we are working on this. Because of this, it's best that he goes to a home w/o small children. This little boy wants nothing more than to be loved and be able to give his family all the love they can handle.
If you are looking for a sweet little fellow who has a bunch of love to give, then Simba might be the one for you.For more information on our adoptable pet list please visit: Adoptable Pet List

Please join us at our next Event(s):

Current Scheduled Events:

animal.description:
Scroll down to learn more about this pet:

***
Bichon and Little Buddies is open only

by appointment with a completed application.
Dogs in foster homes require an appointment and approved application to meet. The application is online at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog If a dog is listed as available, then we are still taking applications - no need to email or call to ask about the status. Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Grace

Breed: Mixed - Possible Jack Russel/Shih Tzu

Approximate Age: 2-3 yr

Gender: Female

Weight:

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Owner surrender

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Grace was surrendered to another individual by her owner, who then transferred her to us so we could find her a great home. Because of this we don't have a background or history on her, and don't know how she is with other dogs or children. If she is scared or nervous she tends to be a little standoffish, so we are going to recommend a home without young children. When she is comfortable she is a happy, friendly girl that craves attention. If interested in adding Grace to your family, please fill out the preadoption application to start the adoption process. If her listing is online, we are still accepting application as we look for the best situation, not just the first application to come in.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. The application puts you under no obligation to adopt a dog from Bichon and Little Buddies.

Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Pinky

Breed: Mixed (possibly Chihuahua mix)

Approximate Age: 1 yr

Gender: Female

Weight: under 10 lb

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Texas Transfer

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Pinky came to WI from Texas so she could find a loving home. She is a bit of a shy girl but is okay with being handled. She is one of a group of dogs that were surrendered from a hoarder home, so she is used to living with other dogs, but not use to a lot of handling. We don't have any other history on her, so don't know if she was housetrained or if she lived with children. We were told that she shouldn't go to a home with children however. If interested in Pinky, please fill out the pre-adoption application.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Booker and Breezy were surrendered to us after being rescued together in an orchard...these two siblings are about 12 weeks old, Booker is 10.5 pounds and breezy is 13 pounds and we believe they will be medium (20-25 pounds at best when grown) they are mixed breed and are absolutely adorable, they are white with light orange spots and freckles and look to be terrier/chihuahua mix. They are being fostered with other dogs of all sizes and ages as well as respectful children and are young enough to be introduced to cats. They are learning about inside living and are doing great! working on house training and playing with toys...these grateful pups would love to be adopted together if possible and if not, they will be looking for a forever home where they will have another sweet sibling that will be a friend to them. If you would like to meet Breezy and Booker, please apply at yvpr.org/adoption.


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Huckleberry is a 5 month old, Beagle mix that came into the rescue from rural Alabama. While we don't know much about his past, we can tell you that Huckleberry is friendly and gentle. He loves to explore, but is just as content laying in your arms. Huckleberry has been working on basic training and is progressing with housebreaking. He needs to learn some manners when it comes to jumping. He has been well-socialized with other dogs and would love a home with a canine companion. As with any dog, he would benefit from a structured daily routine and continued training once he settles into his new home.

In order to be considered as a potential adopter, we will need you to complete our online application at www.arrus.org. Should we choose to move forward with your family, you will be notified via email within the week. Due to the large volume of applications received, we are no longer able to respond to each and every applicant. We apologize in advance for the inconvenience and appreciate your understanding. 

Additional information and/or medical records for this rescue pet are available and will be reviewed in person should we choose to move forward in scheduling a meet n’ greet. In the meantime, please feel free to follow us on follow us on Instagram (animal_rescue_r_us) and visit our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/arrusadopt for more pictures and posts from his/her foster family. 

HELP US, HELP THEM! Animal Rescue R Us is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. We do not receive county, state or federal funding and rely solely on donations. These donations help offset the cost of routine veterinary care, medical expenses, and other necessities while the rescue animal is in our  care. To make a secure donation, please visit www.arrus.org/donate . Alternatively, you may visit our Amazon Wishlist (http://www.amazon.com/registry/wishlist/C36VRV500R85) for a current list of needed supplies! All donations are tax-deductible and all are greatly appreciated. Thank you for your support!

Tucker was adopted a a young pupper but for some reason the tiny toddler in the home if afraid of him.  It is totally not his fault, but to keep peace in the house the family feels it is best to find Tucker a different forever home.  This is what they say about this boy ,  " Tucker is a playful fun loving dog that just wants his belly to be scratched from sun up to sun down. He is a dog that needs lots of love and affection. He is always seeking your approval and wants to hear what a good boy he is. He is crate trained. He sleeps and eats in his crate, but also uses this as his favorite place to nap or use as a place to hide when he is scared. He is happiest when his crate is covered, but is okay without a cover on it. He loves his crate so much! He is potty trained and almost never has accidents in the house. The only time is once or twice when  he was very excited and it was a tiny amount. He loves children and is very gentle. The only risk with kids around, is they might get kisses on their face or hands!  He sleeps all night in his covered crate from usually 9:30-7:30, but will cry out if he needs to potty. This is a rare occasion though. He walks on a leash, but it takes him a bit to warm up to the idea. He has lived with another dog while living with us. They are best friends. They cuddle in their crates, play, and eat together, so he would probably like a playmate in his new home. He barks at squirrels and June bugs, but not at passing neighbors. We have had a few visitor dogs too, and he seems to love anyone he meets. (Animal or human) He has not been around and cats so I’m unsure of how that would go. He is a wonderful boy"      He is about 50 pounds at 8 months.  Might fill out a little but shouldn't be a huge boy when grown.  

Please email adoptions@petsandpeople.com directly for a faster response and we will send you our questionnaire. We get many each day so please watch your spam/trash folders for our replies.

Adoption fee for all dogs and puppies is $130.00 each, which includes spay/neuter, vaccinations (including all puppy boosters for puppies under 4 months), worming, flea/tick treatment if needed, microchip and collar/leash/tags.

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Breezy and Booker were surrendered to us after being rescued together in an orchard...these two siblings are about 12 weeks old,  Booker is 10.5 pounds and breezy is 13 pounds and we believe they will be medium (20-25 pounds at best when grown) they are mixed breed and are absolutely adorable, they are white with light orange spots and freckles and look to be terrier/chihuahua mix. They are being fostered with other dogs of all sizes and ages as well as respectful children and are young enough to be introduced to cats. They are learning about inside living and are doing great! working on house training and playing with toys...these grateful pups would love to be adopted together if possible and if not, they will be looking for a forever home where they will have another sweet sibling that will be a friend to them. If you would like to meet Breezy and Booker, please apply at yvpr.org/adoption.


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Meet Zeke a 4 year old Shepherd mix.  Zeke is a super smart and eager to please boy! He absolutely adores to be by his person and will nudge you for attention.  He came to our rescue after his owner left him abandoned at a local shelter when they could no longer care for him.  This boy deserves to find a family that will give him the love and care he deserves.   He is crate and house trained loves to run and play in the yard.  He would excel in any training classes and would make a wonderful companion.  He knows basic commands like sit and give paw. He needs a family where someone is home more often than not or avid walker/runner.  He is 60lbs and would do best with children 10 years or older due to his larger size.   He would love a fenced in yard but would do well in an apartment or condo with an active owner.   Zeke is current on vaccines, neutered and microchipped.  This very charming boy is ready and waiting for his forever family.   Contact us today at adopt@carolinapaws.com to meet Zeke.  

Adoption fee includes current vaccines, microchip and spay/neuter.  Please review our adoption requirements on our website https://www.carolinapaws.com/adopt/adoption-process/ If interested in one of our rescued cats/dogs complete the online application.  Submitting an application does not obligate you to adopt nor guarantee an adoption.  It is in everyone's best interest to ensure the best possible match, and your cooperation is appreciated. 

We are only accepting applications from the greater Charlotte North Carolina area and certain surrounding counties.

animal.description: Big Foot is a 9 year olf 68lb male Pit bull Mix. He came to us as an owner surrender due to his owner no longer being able to care for him. He is a little shy, but is a friendly boy. He had a mass upon arrival he had removed. We are open by appointment only to ensure we can properly social distance here at the shelter. We cannot guarantee a specific pet or type of pet will be available at your appointment. We do not hold pets. We operate on a first come first serve basis and while you can put what/who you are interested in in the appointment sign up, all appointments are general dog/cat/other animal appointments since we cannot guarantee what will be available at the time of your appointment. If you would like to set up a non-specific dog or cat appointment we have our scheduling system online now at: https://guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/animal-services/animal-shelter/animal-adoption-scheduling All adopted cats and dogs at Guilford County Animal Services come fully up to date on age appropriate vaccines, spayed/neutered, and microchipped. If you are interested in meeting any of our pets, please visit our website to schedule an appointment online. If you believe this may be your pet, please come to the shelter during business hours and bring your ID, proof of ownership, and proof of spay/neuter and/or rabies vaccination history if you have it. See our reclaiming your pet page for more information. If you have any further questions, please contact us at 336-641-3400 or visit our website at https://guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/animal-services/animal-shelter. Thank you for your interest in helping the animals of Guilford County!

Meet Mona, a very pretty, gentle and petite 4-5YO lab whose favorite place in the world is being right next to you! She has all the attributes of a classic lab…smart, gentle, curious, well mannered with a strong desire to love and be loved.  
Mona would LOVE to have a home where a family could spend one on one time with her, spoil her with long walks, long snuggling sessions, and allow her to relax and just be with her. We know that Mona came from a home where multiple dogs, some of them siblings, bullied each other for attention and affection, and it is obvious she was on the receiving side of some of that bullying. So for that reason, the absolute best and only home  for her is one where she will be the only dog, spoiled rotten with all the time and attention she deserves, and finally have the chance of being someones  one and only girl.
If you are ready to have that one special canine love in your heart and home, this sweet girl is very deserving of taking that spot.


We kindly ask that you contact us thru Petfinder or Laura@GreatDawgRescue.org for each dawgs adoption status. We will then follow up with a phone interview and if applicable, send home an Adoption Application.  As always, a Home Visit with you and your family and a Vet Reference will be done prior to placing any of our dawgs to ensure the best match for each dawgs needs. Much thanks!!
https://GreatDawgRescue.org

animal.special_needs_notes:
He had Caval Syndrome. He will need to be on meds to strengthen his heart for life . Roughly $60/month. His operation was successful, He has been heartworm treated and is doing well.

Caval syndrome is a life-threatening complication of heartworm disease, and occurs in approximately 15% of heartworm positive dogs. The presence of worms within the right side of the heart leads to hemolysis and subsequent anemia and pigmenturia necessitating immediate surgical intervention.

animal.description:
Meet Black Betty! She is 9 weeks old and 8-10 pounds (1/26).
                                                                                                                           Do Do you want a family-friendly dog?  Have no fear! Black Betty (BB) is HERE! My five-year-old daughter and Black Betty get along swimmingly. My daughter carries her around, and BB loves the attention. She is extremely playful, cute as a button, and wanting a furrrever home. She cuddles; she has the cutest run/hop ever. She's very friendly to our dogs (30 lb Puggle and 100 lb Bullmastiff).
 She is a puppy & will need typical puppy training to help her learn. We are working on: barking, being mouthy, not jumping up, crate & potty training. She loves affection & treats so training should be a breeze!

Interested in this sweet pup? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

*Please note that all breeds noted are estimates or best guesses. We very rarely have information on our animals' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays*

animal.description:
Hi, my name is mary,  I am 31/2 months old, shih tzu/terrier mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for mary? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting mary.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and mary the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!
animal.name: Mary muller- adoption pending

animal.description:
Hi, my name is  Peter,  I am 31/2 months old, shih tzu/terrier mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Peter? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Peter.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Peter the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
This dog is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $200 if picked up in TN, $250 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Add some sweetness to your life with this chocolate boy, Kodi! He is a 1-year-old, 41 pound Lab mix (best guess) with a fluffy coat and a funny little underbite. Kodi is very loving and friendly, and he gets along well with other dogs and cats. He walks nicely on a leash and is crate trained, and well on his way to being housetrained. Kodi is learning how to cuddle in bed and play with toys as he had never experienced that fun before. His favorite toy right now is a tennis ball, and he has even learned to throw it for himself. He is highly food motivated and will be easy to train with treats. He loves to be close to his people, and his foster mom describes him as a velcro dog. Kodi is eager to please and would be a great hiking running or outdoor activity partner. If you think he sounds like the One, please apply today!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Miss Mikka is a sweet girl who is on the look out for a new home. Mikka would like to be the only pet in her new home as she isn't a fan of cats and she is selective on her dog friends. Mikka LOVES to go for walks and is eager to show her new family around town! This gentle girl can be a bit chatty and isn't well suited for apartment living. She would much prefer to have her own backyard space where she can play between walks!

Mikka has been around children without issue though she has never lived with kids before. Mikka can be left alone for a few hours at a time though she certainly prefers to be around her people. Mikka doesn't show any signs of separation anxiety or resource guarding in shelter or in her previous home. 

Mikka LOVES people, and is eager to say hi to everyone she meets! She will come up to you wiggling her bum with a big tail wag to greet you! If you're looking for a best friend, Mikka is your girl!

We are still getting to know Mikka and will update with new information as we better understand her needs!

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Violet is one of our 4 female pups surrendered to us for adoption 1/22/21
These 4 girls are mixed breed and would be great candidates for a DNA test, we are guessing they have Lab and Chow Chow and a few other breeds in their mix. Violet and Vanya are brindle colored and Violet has a darker brindle and weighs 9.6 lbs.  These pups will be 8+ weeks old and ready for her forever home next weekend 2/6/21
Violet loves her foster family and is with other dogs and a cats, she is with older, respectful children and is quiet and sweet, loves to play and loves her cuddles. If you are looking for a sweet pup to add to your family, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions  


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Posie and I'm sweet and smart and so glad I'm out of  that crowded shelter. I'm still young, estimated DOB 11/9/20) and probably have some heeler in my ancestry. I'm learning so much now that I'm out of that shelter and in a home with other dogs and some considerate children who visit and I love the whole family. I probably would do well with kitties that will tolerate an active puppy.  I'm doing well on my house training and am crate trained.  I'm just a puppy and can get into a lot of trouble so you'll need to be willing to give me lots of gentle guidance, so I can learn all those big dog things, like how to behave in a house, how to walk on a leash without pulling, and all those verbal commands every dog should know. I may even treat people like I treat my sibling with rough play or decide that new pair of shoes or a table leg would make a great chew toy, so a lot of appropriate toys should be in my future. The good news is that with the right training and LOTS of love, I'll be the best addition to your family ever and your best bud. If you are interested in me, please send an email to scpdogworld@gmail.com to get more information on how to fill out an application and have a great meet and greet to see if we are a match made in heaven.

Adopter for this dog must reside in the immediate Houston/Galveston area and be at least 25 years old.  A home visit may be required prior to this dog going to any home. The adoption fee for a dog is $190 (or $245 for puppies) which includes State of Texas sales tax. All dogs are microchipped, on heartworm protection, spayed/neutered, vaccinated, de-wormed and treated for fleas.

Toast is part of a litter dubbed the "Breakfast" pups. This 10 week old, bully mix came into the rescue with his five littermates from rural Alabama. He is super social and loves to play, although, he is just as content being snuggled up in your arms. Toast has been doing well with basic training and sleeps through the night. He has been well-socialized with other dogs and would likely do well in a home with children. As with any dog, Toast would benefit from a structured daily routine and continued training once he settles into his new home.

If you’re looking for an affectionate, playful pup to join your family, Frito may be the guy for you!

FOSTERED IN MISSISSIPPI !!!
My $475 adoption fee includes spay/neuter surgery, vet exam, age appropriate vaccinations, de-worming, flea/tick control, heartworm negative and transport from the south!
I will be ready to travel to a stop near you after my adoption is completed and on 8/8/20. We do not have a facility in NJ or PA to meet before adoption. We ask that you visit your local shelters/rescues first.. We do not adopt to MA or RI or NH residents.

Sweet, happy, energetic, Molly is approx 6-8 months old. She walks on leash, loves her doggy friends, loves attention from her person. Molly is still working on potty training, but she does keep her crate clean overnight without fail. 
Molly is spayed, weighs approx 20-25#, is up to date on all age appropriate vaccines. She will be ready to leave for her new family on 02/05/21. If she is on Petfinder, she is available, please do not ask. 
Please read all of our rescue information throughly.

Apply at : 

http://www.cognitoforms.com/BlessTheirHeartsAnimalRescue/BTHARAdoptionApplication

Like us on Facebook.com/BTHAR2013
For more information on adoption please contact: adoptions.BTHAR@gmail.com


FAQ
frequently asked questions

Is dog/puppy house broke?
Answer: No, all dogs and puppies have been started on house training. They will need more training once they reach your home, unless noted in bio. 

Is dog/puppy been spayed or neutered
Answer:  Yes, every animal that leaves is spayed/neutered. 

Is dog/puppy up to date on vaccines?
Answer: Yes, All animals that leave are up to Age Appropriate vaccines. 

Will I get copies of vet records with the dog/puppy?
Answer: Yes, records will accompany your animal on transport. 

Do you recommend a crate?
Answer: Yes, for the safety of your belongings and them, when they cannot be supervised. 

What has the dog/puppy been eating?
Answer: This information will be provided when adoption is finalized. 

Is the dog/puppy social?
Answer: All of our animals are socialized with other dogs however after life changes they may need a few days to adjust. They are more limited with socializing with strangers due to recent pandemic. 

What is their personality?
Answer: each animals personality’s listen in their bio. 

Is the dog/puppy leash trained? 
Answer: Our older puppies and adults will walk on a leash. Younger puppies will need to be taught by their new family’s.

Hi, my name is Merrick. I am 6lbs(will be bigger fully grown), 2 months old, schnauzer/shih tzu/beagl mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Merrick? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Merrick.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Merrick the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Kingston is a handsome 7-year old male Pit Bull Terrier who arrived at the HSOV on September 21, 2020 after he was picked up in the Cutler Ohio area by the Washington County Dog Warden (and was surrendered by his owner).

Kingston has a brown short smooth coat with a large patch of white on his chest, a long tail, and an adorable face with a splash of white on his muzzle/white stripe on his forehead, a liver-colored nose, and short cropped ears. Kingston was quite friendly when HSOV Kennel tech Kim Cowman accompanied him outdoors for his original photo session on September 22, 2020 :)

The information on Kingston's intake form indicates that he is not good other animals. He apparently was kept indoors since it is noted that Kingston is housebroken.

Kingston weighs 55 lbs and walks fairly well on a leash.

Kingston was neutered on September 30, 2020 and was also given rabies vaccine. Kingston was adopted later that afternoon.

UPDATE: We were saddened when Kingston was returned to our shelter on January 7, 2021. His adopter stated that Kingston did not get along with her other dog.

Kingston appears to have some arthritis (or neurological issues) in his hind legs and hips and also has a slight head tilt these days :( We are listing him as a 'Special Needs Dog' for that reason but we prefer to think of him as merely very special. Kingston still loves to walk with our kennel techs and volunteers and puts forth a noble effort whenever anyone offers him the opportunity for some one-on-one time and attention :)

So this sweet boy is looking for a fabulous home with a compassionate individual or family who will love and cherish him forever and ever.  Kingston has a gentle, lovable personality and is the kind of dog that you want to hold close and promise (as you whisper in his ear) that he will find the best home ever.

These informal photos were taken in the shelter lobby on a rainy afternoon (January 25, 2021) when kennel tech Brad Loyland treated Kingston to some out-of-kennel time shortly before the the shelter staff left for the day.  Kingston enjoyed being the 'center of attention' and being lavished with 'good boy' praises as he carefully made his rounds to each of our kennel techs.  Kingston was so caught up in the moment that he actually came nose-to-nose with Tinker who is one of our free-roaming shelter kitties (and he doesn't even like felines)!

animal.description:
Scout came to us after being found wandering the side of the road in North Carolina. Luckily, he was transported up to Maryland and into our home. He is a wonderfully sweet boy, although he is very shy upon introduction. It took a few days, but he has slowly warmed up to his humans and foster sisters. If you are patient with him he will reward you with his sweet personality.

Scout is a medium energy dog who is equally happy trotting around the yard as he is taking a snooze. So far his favorite activity is curling up on a comfy dog bed while the family watches TV or works from home. He gets along great with his foster sisters and is happy to let them take the lead as he learns the ropes. His gentle and calm disposition would make him a great companion for anyone with a quiet home to offer. He has a ton of love to give in return.

Scout's Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vIndividualCurrentDog.aspx?dogid=69898
Adoptable Dog Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vCurrentDogs.aspx

If you'd like to adopt one of our beagles:
*Go to our Website - href="http://beaglemaryland.org
*Review our  Standards for Adoption - http://beaglemaryland.org/Home.aspx?pg=standardsforadoption.htm
*Fill out an Adopter Profile - 
http://brsmbeagles.org/new_site/documents/BRSM_profile_secure.pdf
 and email it to us (or print it off, fill it in and send it via regular mail, if you prefer)
*A BRSM volunteer will contact you to guide you through the rest of the process!

We hope to hear from you, and so do the beagles!

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
 Valerie is one of our 4 female pups surrendered to us for adoption 1/22/21
These 4 girls are mixed breed and would be great candidates for a DNA test, we are guessing they have Lab and Chow Chow and a few other breeds in their mix. Valerie and Vivian are tan colored and Valerie has a darker ring around her neck and weighs 8.10 lbs.  These pups will be 8+ weeks old and ready for her forever home next weekend 2/6/21
Valerie loves her foster family and is with other dogs and a cats, she is with older, respectful children and is quiet and sweet, loves to play and loves her cuddles. If you are looking for a sweet pup to add to your family, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions 


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Sienna. I am 6lbs(will be bigger fully grown), 2 months old, schnauzer/shih tzu/beagl mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Sienna? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Sienna.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Sienna the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR THE ADOPTION APPLICATION FORM? 
Please visit our website at: www.LHAR.dog 

If application is approved, pup will be held for you to meet/adopt within a few days of application approval! 


(Appointment will be scheduled after application is approved) 

Location: WagsMore Adopt & Shop
                  450 Prospect Blvd, Frederick MD 21701
 
Age of pup: approx 1 year old of February 2021
   
The adoption donation for these pups: is $375.00

This includes: Age appropriate vaccines and dewormings, rabies vaccine, HW prevention and neuter

Size:  large when full grown 
Breed: Husky/Retriever mix is best guess?

Petfinder's Dog Size Recommendations:

Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

Please note our requirements to adopt a young puppy. 

1. Fill out our online application at: Www.LHAR.dog 

2. We require all current pets in the household to be up to date on shots and be spayed/neutered. Veterinary references will be contacted. 

3. We require that someone be in the home/work from home half of the work day throughout the work week. It is not healthy for a puppy to be crated and left alone for 5 or more hours a day. Lunch breaks are not considered home half the work day and asking a neighbor to stop in is not considered home half the day. 

Their Story: 

LHAR rescued these sweeet brothers with the help of an organization in rural WV. The are affectionate and submissive pups who love attention and wrestling with each other. We have no confirmed history of Mom or Dad. We believe they are husky/lab mixes. They were likely outdoor dogs before coming to LHAR. They are working on their house training and leash skills. Will require secure and tall fencing or leash walks only. We would love to see them be homed together, but could be seperated. 
  
They are being fostered together in a private home 

Weight: approx 50 lbs bs as of January 31st        
 
Photos were taken on January 31st    

Questions? Please email: lharinfo@gmail.com

Adoption donation fees: Please know that 100% of our fees go towards the rescue of puppies and dogs in need. Lonely Hearts Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non profit organization.

Thank you for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description: Millie is a 6-year-old 30 lb, Springer Spaniel Mix.  Millie was relinquished to a shelter in rural North Carolina due to the family having financial issues and unable to continue caring for this sweet soul.  Millie was severely matted, scared and it was found that she has a chain of mammary masses.  She just underwent surgery and we'll know more in a few days about the status of the biopsy.  With all of the hurdles, Millie is precious and we are looking for that special family who can care for her while she's healing and has the financial ability to keep her groomed regularly.  Millie is said to be good with other dogs but she has not been child or cat tested yet.  We are awaiting transport to us at this time but accepting applications for foster/adopt.  Please reach out to adoptsch@gmail.com for an application.

animal.description:
Kankel is a 5 month old, 23 pound Pittie puppy who is the life of the party! This girl is constantly on the go, ready to make new friends. She loves nothing more than running and playing with the other dogs in her foster home. Her favorite thing is being chased around the yard while her little legs carry her as quick as they can! Kankel isn't picky about her toys and will play with anything she's given! She's working hard on crate and potty training but will need continued work in her forever home. Kankel loves to give out kisses and is working on her manners. Due to her energy level, Kankel would do best in a home without toddlers, as she may accidentally knock over a small kid in her excitement. While she has not been exposed to cats, she would likely do well with a dog-savvy cat! This girl is a bundle of energy who is ready to find that perfect forever home that will teach her tricks and help burn off her energy. If you want to make Kankel a part of your family, apply online today!

My adoption fee is $400.

animal.description:
Meet the Bridgerton Crew! Lady Violet Bridgerton (momma dog) had eight healthy babies that came into rescue. She had four boys (Colin, Gregory, Anthony and Benedict) and four girls (Eloise, Hyacinth, Daphne and Francesca).

Violet is in a foster home with other dogs, but is protective right now due to her puppies, so she is kept apart from them. She does not like cats and will chase them. Violet is shy upon meeting you, but then will melt in your arms and prefers to be held like a baby. Violet is a cuddle bug and will love to chill on your lap all day. She uses a dog door and enjoys sleeping in a crate. She is working on her leash manners and knows basic commands. Violet is great at jumping baby gates and will go exploring if given the opportunity. The only time Violet barks is when she is letting you know someone is approaching the home.

If you are interested in Violet, please fill out an application on our website so we can arrange a home check and meet/greet.

Her adoption fee is $150 which will include her spay, 5-in-1 vaccine, Rabies vaccine, microchip and dewormer.

animal.description:
Muffin is part of a litter dubbed the "Breakfast" pups. This 10 week old, bully mix came into the rescue with her five littermates from rural Alabama. While we don't know much about her past, we can tell you that this little lady is friendly, playful, and affectionate. She loves to play with her toys and is just as content being snuggled up in your arms. Muffin has been well-socialized with other dogs and would likely do well in a home with children. As with any dog, she would benefit from a structured daily routine and continued training once she settles into her new home.

In order to be considered as a potential adopter, we will need you to complete our online application at www.arrus.org. Should we choose to move forward with your family, you will be notified via email within the week. Due to the large volume of applications received, we are no longer able to respond to each and every applicant. We apologize in advance for the inconvenience and appreciate your understanding. 

Additional information and/or medical records for this rescue pet are available and will be reviewed in person should we choose to move forward in scheduling a meet n’ greet. In the meantime, please feel free to follow us on follow us on Instagram (animal_rescue_r_us) and visit our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/arrusadopt for more pictures and posts from his/her foster family. 

HELP US, HELP THEM! Animal Rescue R Us is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. We do not receive county, state or federal funding and rely solely on donations. These donations help offset the cost of routine veterinary care, medical expenses, and other necessities while the rescue animal is in our  care. To make a secure donation, please visit www.arrus.org/donate . Alternatively, you may visit our Amazon Wishlist (http://www.amazon.com/registry/wishlist/C36VRV500R85) for a current list of needed supplies! All donations are tax-deductible and all are greatly appreciated. Thank you for your support!

animal.description:
Peaches is part of a litter dubbed the "Breakfast" pups. This 10 week old, bully mix came into the rescue with her five littermates from rural Alabama. While we don't know much about her past, we can tell you that this little lady is friendly, playful, and affectionate. She loves to play with her toys and is just as content being snuggled up in your arms. Peaches has been well-socialized with other dogs and would likely do well in a home with children. As with any dog, she would benefit from a structured daily routine and continued training once she settles into her new home.

In order to be considered as a potential adopter, we will need you to complete our online application at www.arrus.org. Should we choose to move forward with your family, you will be notified via email within the week. Due to the large volume of applications received, we are no longer able to respond to each and every applicant. We apologize in advance for the inconvenience and appreciate your understanding. 

Additional information and/or medical records for this rescue pet are available and will be reviewed in person should we choose to move forward in scheduling a meet n’ greet. In the meantime, please feel free to follow us on follow us on Instagram (animal_rescue_r_us) and visit our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/arrusadopt for more pictures and posts from his/her foster family. 

HELP US, HELP THEM! Animal Rescue R Us is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. We do not receive county, state or federal funding and rely solely on donations. These donations help offset the cost of routine veterinary care, medical expenses, and other necessities while the rescue animal is in our  care. To make a secure donation, please visit www.arrus.org/donate . Alternatively, you may visit our Amazon Wishlist (http://www.amazon.com/registry/wishlist/C36VRV500R85) for a current list of needed supplies! All donations are tax-deductible and all are greatly appreciated. Thank you for your support!

animal.description:
ADOPTION INFO:
FOSTERED IN MISSISSIPPI !!!
My $475 adoption fee includes spay/neuter surgery, vet exam, age appropriate vaccinations, de-worming, flea/tick control, heartworm negative and transport from the south!
I will be ready to travel to a stop near you after my adoption is completed and on 8/8/20. We do not have a facility in NJ or PA to meet before adoption. We ask that you visit your local shelters/rescues first.. We do not adopt to MA or RI or NH residents.

Anna Bea is a sweet little girl who we believe to be a chihuahua/dachshund mix. Anna Bea weighs approx 10# and is full grown. She is 1-2 yrs old and has been spayed. She is a loving girl who enjoys being inside with her person or making outside jaunts with supervision. She really doesn’t like to go out alone. Anna Bea does very well with her potty manners again with supervision. She gets along well with other dogs and kitties. She can be timid until comfortable and sometimes your size is intimidating, so you must sit or squat down when calling her to you. Once she is familiar with her person, she is fine. 
Please do not apply for Anna Bea if you are not willing to give her ample time to adjust. Chihuahua’s often require that. Chihuahua experience is preferred for this girl and no small children due to her size. 
If she is listed, she is available. First step to adoption is an application. Please read all information regarding our rescue throughly. 

Apply at : 

http://www.cognitoforms.com/BlessTheirHeartsAnimalRescue/BTHARAdoptionApplication

Like us on Facebook.com/BTHAR2013
For more information on adoption please contact: adoptions.BTHAR@gmail.com


FAQ
frequently asked questions

Is dog/puppy house broke?
Answer: No, all dogs and puppies have been started on house training. They will need more training once they reach your home, unless noted in bio. 

Is dog/puppy been spayed or neutered
Answer:  Yes, every animal that leaves is spayed/neutered. 

Is dog/puppy up to date on vaccines?
Answer: Yes, All animals that leave are up to Age Appropriate vaccines. 

Will I get copies of vet records with the dog/puppy?
Answer: Yes, records will accompany your animal on transport. 

Do you recommend a crate?
Answer: Yes, for the safety of your belongings and them, when they cannot be supervised. 

What has the dog/puppy been eating?
Answer: This information will be provided when adoption is finalized. 

Is the dog/puppy social?
Answer: All of our animals are socialized with other dogs however after life changes they may need a few days to adjust. They are more limited with socializing with strangers due to recent pandemic. 

What is their personality?
Answer: each animals personality’s listen in their bio. 

Is the dog/puppy leash trained? 
Answer: Our older puppies and adults will walk on a leash. Younger puppies will need to be taught by their new family’s.
