animal.description:
Hi, my name is Garland. I am 6lbs(will be bigger fully grown), 2 months old, schnauzer/shih tzu/beagl mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Garland? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Garland.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Garland the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Sweet little Della decided she would hunt no more, forever. So her owner didn't want her anymore. But she is a really nice girl, so she came to Beagle Rescue. She's rather shy, but is motivated by treats and enjoys being petted. She only just arrived, so stay tuned for more info about her personality. We want to see her let her hair down a bit so we see her true personality and know what kind of home she needs.
Update 01/23/21
She’s still very skittish - she’s leaning about what it means to live indoors. TV noise, opening the refrigerator, the Roomba - it’s all still a little scary but she makes good progress every day! She is now peeing and pooping in the backyard but won’t go on the leash (yet). She does walk nicely on a leash by herself and with my two others. She likes my other dogs and is very submissive. She’s been eating well and enjoys getting a treat but sometimes she’s too scared to take it from your hard. She enjoys being pet and will roll on to her back for attention. She slept through the night last night. She’s gone in the crate with mixed results but she does like a “cave” to nap in.

She not outgoing personality wise or super eager to please so I’m not sure agility would be something she would want to do. She is incredibly sweet and just needs to learn about indoor living and life with people.

Della's Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vIndividualCurrentDog.aspx?dogid=69900
Adoptable Dog Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vCurrentDogs.aspx

If you'd like to adopt one of our beagles:
*Go to our Website - href="http://beaglemaryland.org
*Review our  Standards for Adoption - http://beaglemaryland.org/Home.aspx?pg=standardsforadoption.htm
*Fill out an Adopter Profile - 
http://brsmbeagles.org/new_site/documents/BRSM_profile_secure.pdf
 and email it to us (or print it off, fill it in and send it via regular mail, if you prefer)
*A BRSM volunteer will contact you to guide you through the rest of the process!

We hope to hear from you, and so do the beagles!

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Vivian is one of our 4 female pups surrendered to us for adoption 1/22/21
These 4 girls are mixed breed and would be great candidates for a DNA test, we are guessing they have Lab and Chow Chow and a few other breeds in their mix. Vivian and Valerie are tan colored and Vivian is lighter and weighs 8.06 lbs.  These pups will be 8+ weeks old and ready for her forever home next weekend 2/6/21
Vivian loves her foster family and is with other dogs and a cat, she is with older, respectful children and is quiet and sweet, loves to play and loves her cuddles. If you are looking for a sweet pup to add to your family, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions  


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Hi, my name is  Summit,  I am 5lbs(will be bigger fully grown), 2 months old, schnauzer/shih tzu/beagl mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Summit? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Summit.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Summit the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Meet the Bridgerton Crew! Lady Violet Bridgerton (momma dog) had eight healthy babies that came into rescue. She had four boys (Colin, Gregory, Anthony and Benedict) and four girls (Eloise, Hyacinth, Daphne and Francesca). Unfortunately, we do not know who their dad is. All furbabies are happy, healthy and growing big. They are in a foster home where they are exposed to other big and small dogs, kids, and lots of human contact. They are in the beginning stages of crate training and know what a dog door is.

We prefer they go to homes with other active dogs and an active family that will teach them puppy manners. They are not potty trained yet and chew on things they don't know aren't toys. They are eating puppy kibble and are weaned from mom. If you are interested in a puppy, please fill out an application on our website so we can arrange a home check and meet/greet.

Their adoption fee is $300 which will include their spay/neuter, 3-4 sets of puppy vaccines, Rabies vaccine, microchip and dewormer (all age appropriate).

MEET ROXY!!

Roxy was very spoiled by her owner. They recently had a new baby and  have realized that Roxy is not fond of babies or young children so Roxy needs a new home where she is the baby and can be the center of attention!

We are looking for a home that has the time and attention to give her with children under 10yrs. 

Roxy is a 4 years old Dachshund/Jack Russell blend!

Roxy is very sweet and affectionate and great with people, other dogs and cats!!

Roxy is housetrained and crate trained and loves car rides! She is great at the groomers! 

She is smart and knows how to sit, shake and up!

Roxy is affectionate and loving and LOVES attention from her person and likes to be touching someone, whether it is her paw or sitting on you! 

THIS GIRL IS A GEM!!!

mini-mutts@outlook.com

(fosters/adopters must be in the Dallas/Fort Worth/Rockwall or surrounding areas only)
**************************************
*NO CHILDREN UNDER 10 YRS OLD
*************************************
TO APPLY-Your dog’s heartworm prevention and testing must be seen on vet records or other proof must be included. The records must show 2 years of continuous prevention on current dogs.

Your application will NOT be approved without this documentation.

***If NO PREVIOUS DOG history we require the purchase of one year supply of heartworm prevention. (cost $40) added onto adoption fee. ***

animal.description:
**Please read Amelia's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

This young lady is Amelia, a 1-year old, 35-pound Treeing Walker Coonhound mix who needs a gentle touch.

Amelia is a very sweet, good natured, and playful. She loves playing with her toys, which she mostly throws up in the air or across the room. 
She is friendly with all dogs and cats. Every morning when she gets up, before going potty, she has to go through the house to tell all the other dogs and cats good morning.  

Amelia likes going on walks, but she absolutely loves snuggling hugs and kisses. 

She does need a gentle touch because she doesn’t do well with a raised voices. She can be shy and skittish around new experiences.  Since she loves kind words and hugs, she gets nervous if there is shouting or yelling. 

If you are an easy going family who enjoys playing outdoors and then snuggling on the couch, Amelia will fit right in.

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Amelia, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Vanya is one of our 4 female pups surrendered to us for adoption 1/22/21
These 4 girls are mixed breed and would be great candidates for a DNA test, we are guessing they have Lab and Chow Chow and a few other breeds in their mix. Vanya and Violet are fluffy brindles and Vanya is a lighter color and weighs 8.10 lbs.  These pups will be 8+ weeks old and ready for her forever home next weekend 2/6/21
Vanya loves her foster family and is with other dogs and a cat, she is with older, respectful children and is quiet and sweet, loves to play and loves her cuddles. If you are looking for a sweet pup to add to your family, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions  


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for. animal.description:
Willie Nelson, 2 year, 42 pounds

Willie Nelson is an active, 42 pound doggo who loves attention. He is a smart boy and a quick learner. He sits when asked and will settle down to hang out with you after he's had his exercise. He would like daily walks or a secure yard to romp in, but we would not suggest leaving him alone outdoors as he is an avid fence climber. Willie does have a bit of separation anxiety. He would not be a good candidate for crate training, as he has been known to injure his nose trying to get out of the crate. Willie would do best in a household where someone is home most of the time. He wants to be your only fur-kid and no children. If you're looking for a buddy to spend lots of time with then meet Willie Nelson!

If interested, visit THHS.org. Click on Willie's picture to find the adopt me link to the application. A staff member will review all applications and if approved will call you to set up a meet and greet appointment. For questions please email adopt@THHS.org

ADOPTION INCLUDES: Spay or Neuter,Worming,Vaccinations (excluding rabies), Microchip, Free Vet visit at Participating Offices, 30 Days of Health Insurance provided by PetHealth (some restrictions apply). Adoption Fees may vary, but our standard fees are: Kittens and Cats $85, Puppies $175, and Dogs $125. We offer Discounts on Senior Animals and Special Needs Animals. We also offer special incentives for Seniors and Military.

She had four boys (Colin, Gregory, Anthony and Benedict) and four girls (Eloise, Hyacinth, Daphne and Francesca). Unfortunately, we do not know who their dad is. We prefer they go to homes with other active dogs and an active family that will teach them puppy manners. They are not potty trained yet and chew on things they don't know aren't toys. They are eating puppy kibble and are weaned from mom. If you are interested in a puppy, please fill out an application on our website so we can arrange a home check and meet/greet.

animal.description:
Cookie is so gentle and SO sweet and affectionate. She is about 6 or 7 years old and 40 lbs of love. She is still very playful and is great with other dogs (we can cat test). Cookie is snuggly and just an all round wonderful companion. She has clearly had too many litters of puppies, but that is all over and done with now. She is just a super companion dog, in need of a loving forever home. A must meet, for she will steal your heart for sure. CRPUPS@PTD.NET to contact us for any reason. (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there might be something wrong with your email! WE DO NOT TEXT) 
Lovable Mutts Adoption Center is a private, in home, all breed rescue/adoption facility, specializing in all ages and sizes of dogs.  We exist only on the kindness of your donations and adoptions!  We pride ourselves on being an HOLISTIC center and feed only holistic grain free foods and give daily, various, vitamins and supplements to all of our dogs. 

Our dogs are well socialized, very friendly, well mannered, affectionate, and in wonderful health. While some might be timid or shy, we work with our adopters in any way we can, to help them to work with their new family member. We give training tips and behavioral tips and even board for a very reasonable fee. Our dogs are extremely well cared for - most even know how to use a dog door by the time they leave us, know basic commands, and are crate trained!  We stand by our pups/dogs, and give 10 days for a refund and almost always take our dogs back at any age of their lives (can sometimes depend on the dog)! 

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center has an application screening process.  All applicants are asked to provide vet references, personal references, and a home visit.  We pride ourselves in matching up the right dog with the right home.  Sometimes this happens quickly and sometimes it might take awhile.  We hope you understand and are willing to wait for the perfect pup for your situation. We reserve the right to turn applicants down and to change our mind about a suitable match, for we are only concerned about what is best for our dogs.  Also note that we arrange our visiting hours around your schedule, as this is a private, in home facility.  We respond to all inquiries promptly, so if you have any trouble sending us an email, or have not heard back from us within 24 hours, please, CONTACT US AGAIN and check your spam!  (We all know how emails can be at times!)

Our dogs are spayed or neutered (if old enough), up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested, and free of fleas and ticks.  We temperament test our  dogs and they are all suitable for many family situations. Our dogs are well mannered,  and are in our family/home situation at this time (not kept in kennels or crates), and are worked with daily.  All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats, and we can cat test. Adoption donations vary with age, breed, vetting, and training of the dog, and range from $250 to $500. This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care.  (We do not tend to place puppies or small dogs with kids under 6 and reserve the right to match who WE feel would be the best homes for our dogs.)  
Please, come adopt one of our Lovable Mutts - you will be so glad you did!

(IF YOU DO NOT GET A REPLY EMAIL WITHIN 24 HOURS, CHECK YOUR SPAM BOX - WE REPLY EVERY FEW HOURS TO EMAILS)

animal.description: Hi there! My name is Elena and I am so excited you're here! I'm looking for the perfect forever home with a human that has lots of time to play, pet, and cuddle with me. Oh, and an endless supply of tasty treats. I know I'm ready to go home with you so, what are you waiting for? I am full grown at ~20 lbs. Cats/Children? Unknown. Dogs? I may do best as your one and only. Housetrained? I've almost got it! Training needs? I bet I can learn anything you want to teach me with the right treats! Energy level? Low to medium. How did I get here? Adopted and returned due to some dog selective behaviors. ~My adoption fee is $95.00.~

animal.description:
Riley, 3.5 year old terrier blend. Up to date on vaccinations, altered, and microchipped. 45lbs. 

She gets along great woth other dogs and children, unsure about cats. 

She has been known to climb fences, so she should not be left unattended. 

To fill out an application please visit our website www.laurashoperescue.com


1. This rescue is run out of a private home please do not email asking to meet the dog unless you have an application submitted or you have an application that has been approved 6months or less
2.  The information that we have is current and to the best of our knowledge when we learn more about the dog's personality we immediately post that.
3.   All of our dogs are good with school-age children. And will do fine with that as long as your child is good and respects dogs boundaries
4. Please visit our Facebook page. Pictures and updates are posted there first.  

5. All of our rescue dogs have the following

Spay or neuter certificates

vaccination records including Rabies

Are on a monthly flea and heartworm preventive. 

Crate leash and house trained. 

Get along with other dogs ( otherwise indicated )

Enjoy the company of school-age children who are respectful to them 

Most of them enjoy the company of cats as well, HOWEVER, in the past, we have found out that for some reason that is not always the case.  

We work VERY hard making sure our dogs acclimate to their new homes.  We seek adopters whose current pets are current on vaccinations and are altered. {

PLEASE do not fill out an application if your pets are not. You will be denied.


Applications can be found by going to our website  www.laurashoperescue.com

We hope to hear from you, and so do the beagles!

animal.description:
Meet Baxter, an adorable 10 year old, 13 pound Yorkie boy being fostered in Liberty Hill, TX. Due to COVID concerns, only Texas applicants will be considered.

BIO UPDATE: 01/25/21. Baxter had surgery last week for his neuter and to fix the hole in the roof of his mouth. The vet has no idea how it happened, however it is definitely from an injury. The vet performed a skin graft, however 3 days later Baxter somehow managed to rip the stitches and the hole is back. He has a consultation with a specialist on February 2, where they'll tell us what can be done. He's eating well, now that the foster mom has found a thick pate he can just swallow that doesn't go into his sinuses. He's a happy boy who loves sleeping in foster mom and dad's bed, and demands belly rubs in the morning upon waking up. Potty training is going well, and he even has asked to go outside a few times.

Baxter would be happy in a home as an only dog, or small dogs (he gets along with those fine). Cats and larger dogs we would not recommend. He is also great with kids. Foster mom will update more after his consultation! If you'd like more info on Baxter, you can reach her at rescuesreallyrock@gmail.com.

INITIAL BIO. 12/08/20. Howdy! My name is Baxter. Nice to meet you! I had been residing in a shelter in North Texas, where I was taken as I was roaming the streets. No one has come to get me though, so the nice folks at UYR took me in! My foster mom just got me groomed and oh my gosh do I feel and look better! Like, is there a Tinder for dogs? (Oh, won't need that as they're getting me neutered next week anyway....oh well). My foster mom said she'll know more about how house trained I am after that...I will say I have not done #2 in the house! I even asked to go outside last night.

One fun fact about me is that I have no teeth. I think it makes me pretty special (hello, cute tongue hanging out)! My foster mom found a nice thick pate she cuts up that I can eat just fine! I need to gain some weight so that's perfect for me (I'm about 11 lbs right now...and gaining!). I get along great with other dogs....my foster family has 2 small and 2 big ones; I like 'em all! Cats? Not so much. I like their human kids, though! They give me belly rubs a lot....that's a favorite. I do sleep all night in a little bed they got me that is next to their bed.

As far as my age....well, I am not sure! The dogtor says I am "middle aged". My foster mom is too, and she said that's a pretty good age to be. If you think you may be the right furever home for me, you can reach out to my foster mom at rescuesreallyrock@gmail.com. Thanks!

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Prince Brownie and I'm technically a 2 year old Chow, but my foster dad just calls me a 60lb ball of fluff. I really enjoy hanging around with my humans, but also love to zoom around with other dogs. I used to be a little leery of being inside of a house because I grew up outside, but I have quickly gotten used to the idea of being inside and don't want to ever go back. I currently am living with a 30 lb puppy Golden Retriever and a 60lb Boxer, and we get along great! I was not very used to being walked on a leash when I first got here, but I've been working on it and have made tremendous progress. I'm really just looking for someone that will feed me, because I really like food. It doesn't matter what kind of food either, seriously I will be best friends with whoever will feed me the most. I'm pretty big into cuddling, so if you're looking to find someone to hang out on the couch and snack with, I am your guy and you should fill out an application today! My adoption fee is $250.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
**Please read Meiko's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Meet Meiko, a 3-year old, 50-pound Catahoula Leopard Dog/American Bulldog mix gal.

Meiko is a very sweet loving girl who has not had an easy early life. Her prior owners bred her often. In her last litter she had only two pups that were very weak and died. The owners then surrendered Meiko to a rescue center because she was no longer producing puppies for them. 

Meiko quickly acclimated to her foster home. She gets along great with other dogs, loves attention, getting petted, lounging about and being with her people. 

She has been around older children. She will make a great gal who likes to go on walks then lay on the couch with her people. 

She has an adorable voice and can be a “talker.” (She’s not a barker at all, but will talk for attention). 

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Meiko, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

animal.description:
Hey there, Heinicke here! I was tired of life on the streets, so one day I followed a nice stranger home and after hanging out on the porch for a while together, we met some nice people who took me to HRA. I'm a super friendly guy who loves to be petted. If you sit down near me, you are likely to find my paws placed gently in your lap and my happy face looking to gain your attention. My foster dad, Nathaniel, bought me a bunch of fun toys and I like to play with them, the Kong in particular, but I'm really more interested in spending time with a human. I have been with my foster dad for a few days now and have been acclimating quite well. Because I have lots of energy and lovins to give, we're working on sit, stay, down, and place so I can calm down when I need to. I'm super food-motivated which is great because I'm learning a lot! While I really don't love the lead collar Nathaniel's using when we walk, I am not pulling on leash as much! While on leash, I'm not very interested in other creatures like dogs, squirrels, or little humans; I just go about my merry way, wagging my little hiney as we go along. I also think I'll be best for a loving family who doesn't have other dogs -- I have more than enough love to share on my own! 

For more info, or to virtually meet me, contact AdoptHeinicke@gmail.com.

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Velvet. I am a 1.5 year old girl and I weigh 8lbs. My foster mom says I might be a small spitz mix...or a vampire. My little teeth like to stick out of my mouth and it looks like I am smiling! I love to cuddle and be pet, but my favorite thing to do is wrestle with my foster sister and chase her around the house and yard. I have a lot of puppy energy, so I need a friend who will play with me. I am potty trained and know the doggy door. I sleep quietly in my crate at night, but don't like it so much when you leave, so an apartment would not be a good home fore me. I will chew on things I'm not supposed to, so I need to be crated when you are not watching me. But I listen very well if you tell me to stop it. I am learning not to jump and get under foster moms feet, but I still need a lot of reminders because I just get so darn excited to see her! I am eager to learn, and eager to please, so a basic training class would be super duper fun for me! I am shy at first, so I would also like to work more on meeting new people. My ideal family would be active and lots of fun!

animal.description:
KOOKIE is a sweetie...male, Dachshund mix, about 7 mos old (DOB: 6/15/20.  In foster in W Wa. He weighs 13.80#.  He's a little shy to strangers but warms up with food.  He was owned by a little old lady that no longer could keep him.  She never did officially name him but would always ask him if he wanted a "cookie" and he started thinking that was his name.  So...to keep him a 'boy'... I named him Kookie.  He will make a good pet/companion for a couple or single person.  I wouldn't recommend children because of his shyness.  He does like to sleep on my bed.  He's just a sweetie.  We are working on house training.

This dog is available now to pre adopt directly from us the rescue in TX.  Adoptions include neuter/spay, vaccinations (DHPP, Bordetella, Rabies), microchip, transport with OUR professional dog transporter, and 6 mos of heartworm prevention. You can ask us about how pre adoption works and our 'trial period'.

If you have any questions, text me...  210-394-6060.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out the on-line application. Yes you must COPY and PASTE the application link .
http://shaynesrescue.com/adoption-application-pet-central-satx/

You can also go to our Facebook page...
https://www.facebook.com/Pet-Central-SATX-866684826744181/
and LIKE us to help us out.

GET IN LINE FIRST: If you are interested in this dog, please fill out the application (link listed above). The rescue will contact you once the application is received. Although we strive to answer everyone, due to the high volume of inquiries we receive, we cannot guarantee a response to all emails. Filling out the application is the ONLY way to ensure a response from the rescue. In addition, while you are emailing us, if others apply, you lose out adopting the dog you chose. We have hundreds of puppies/dogs available so there really is no need to apply anywhere else.  Also, one application is good even if you are interested in several different dogs...one application no matter which one you choose.  We try to make it as easy as possible for you but if you are applying or have applied anywhere else, we do need to know that, too.

SHANYE'S FOSTERS is a group of foster parents in the Olympia/Tumwater area. We foster dogs for rescues and assist them in adopting/rehoming of their pups/dogs by listing on this site. Many dogs posted here are available to pre adopt NOW directly from the rescue. The only ones in foster in the NW specifically state that. We have very few fosters so most need to be pre adopted. All adoption fees go towards rescuing more dogs in need. No one receives a salary. Shayne's Fosters is not responsible for any experience you have with any dog you might see posted on this site. They are the property of the sponsoring rescue who will supply all medical supporting records which is given with each dog when adopted.

Our adoption fees cover all medical costs to make sure the pups are appropriately vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and spayed/ neutered. It also covers the cost of transport from Texas and the necessary health certificate documentation. The fees also include a negative heartworm test for any dogs over 6 months. Some dogs have additional medical, such as FHO, ACL, hernias, dental, and a myriad of other vetting.  We do full disclosure of medical care/situations. If the adoption fees seem high (which never cover the true cost of rescue), we recommend fostering for a good rescue. Fostering ensures you incur no vet bills and no boarding fees. We are always in need of good fosters. We are all volunteers who donate our time and resources to help save as many dogs/pups lives as we possibly can.

Thank you for choosing to adopt a rescue pup/dog. Over 1 billion dogs worldwide are put to sleep (PTS) annually... thousands daily.  The dog pounds PTS entire litters, pregnant/nursing moms and wonderful dogs that can make someone a great companion. We firmly believe there is NO breed other than "rescue" for all species. Thank you for being part of the village it takes to save these precious lives.

animal.description:
Easy, Breezy, Beautiful. Miss Breezy encompasses all those traits! Breezy was found as a stray having her puppies by a dumpster. She is slowly learning how live in a home and be a pet. 
Expected to be about 2-3 years old and some sort of hound mix weighing 48lbs full grown. 
She is potty trained and does wonderfully left out alone in the house for the day while no one is home. 
She is timid with new people and scared of loud noises, but every day  with reassurance from her foster family, she is learning that not everyone is like the people who let her down leaving her on her own. 
She loves just lounging around the house, snuggling up to you if you are near. She’s learning to love pets, and adores having her ears rubbed. 
We haven’t figured out toys yet, but she does like to carry them around. She is very curious and wants to learn as much as she can and will follow you around the house investigating everything you do. 
Breezy is heartworm positive and is beginning treatment. She will be scheduled to be spayed after that, so no more puppies for this sweet momma! 
She is good with other dogs and older kids. We’re not sure about cats. 
She would love for you to open up your home and be your sweet snuggly shadow!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

My name is Sweet Pea, and I'm around 2 years old and a petite 28 pounds.  I'm all set to join my new family - already spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations.  

I'm new to PAC, but before I made the trip here, the wonderful people in Arkansas got to know me pretty well. Here are some things they wanted to pass along about me: 

'Sweet Pea was originally a stray. She had found her way to an elderly gentleman's house where she was taken care of for several months. Sweet Pea is an amazing dog but was just too energetic for the elderly man. She walks on a leash, is house trained, can use a dog door and a crate. She's been good with other dogs, did very good with children, playful and very social. She's loving, eager to engage and play with everyone and has a happy wiggly sweet disposition.'

So do I sound like your new BFF??!  Then, if you are interested in meeting me, please schedule an appointment here: ProvidenceAC.org/AdoptADog. My paws are crossed I will see you very soon! 
XOXO Sweet Pea"

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!

animal.description:
Cookie is as scrumptious as a fresh batch of her namesake coming right out of the oven, all gooey and warm. She is a young mid-sized girl who loves people, dogs and playtime. Cookie is searching for her perfect home with a canine companion and a fenced-in yard for them to play in. She rides well in the car, and knows "sit", "lay down" and "come". She is still working on her leash skills and not getting overly excited and jumping when she makes new friends. She is treat motivated, which should make learning these things a breeze, and takes her treats so sweetly. Cookie also knows not to beg for food. While she may be hesitant to go in her crate - she'd rather be where her family is! - she does settle down and behave nicely inside and will sleep through the night. Cookie would prefer an adult only home, preferring a bit less chaos and a lot more love. So pour yourself a big ole' glass of milk and submit your adoption request at savinggracenc.org to meet Cookie!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Leamon! Born around December 2017, he is a smaller guy with an optimal weight around 75 pounds.

This poor boy has had a rough life. He was found as a stray when he wandered up to people setting up a fireworks stand on the outskirts of Dallas. He was thin, had no collar, an injured eye, and seemed to have trouble with his hind leg. After some trepidation and escaping a new collar, he rode home in the lap of his rescuer.

Leamon's medical evaluation revealed that his pelvis had an old break causing leg pain. Due to the age of the injury, surgery is not an option. He happily takes a joint supplement and fish oil with his kibbles. These aids help prevent the pain. He may occasionally require meloxicam if he becomes sore.

Leamon needs to maintain his healthy weight to keep his hips from hurting. He will have trouble if he becomes chubby.

He also has an old eye injury that also does not need surgery. The eye appears small, but he still has some limited vision in it. He tends to be easily surprised when things come at him from that side.

On top of all that, he has some old hot spots and red stains on his fur from not eating right. He also has allergies to chicken products. Luckily, his skin and coat are clearing up as he continues his new healthy food intake.

Sweet Leamon is initially shy around new people, but he warms up quickly. He's been getting braver every day.

He is definitely more confident and outgoing with dogs than with people. He is nice to canines and cats. He plays with toys for short periods of time.

Leamon is house trained and crate trained. While he was at first very opposed to leashes, he now accepts them, and his leash work is improving as he builds confidence.

Leamon needs a lower energy home without stairs. Because he startles easily due to his limited vision, a home without small children would be best.

It may take some time for him to become the beautiful dog he is meant to be. He will soon have a gorgeous coat to match his long fan tail.

SPIN Pyrs are all in foster homes in the Dallas/Fort Worth area. Potential adopters are asked to make travel arrangements if they live elsewhere. All SPIN dogs are spayed or neutered, current on vaccinations and on heartworm prevention. Please go to our website www.SpinRescue.org and fill out an application for this great Great Pyrenees!

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete an adoption application. 
Wiley is a 12 week old mixed breed female puppy that is sable and tan, has a dense coat and currently weighs 15.5 pounds. She came to us after being found and weighing under 1 pound, she was syringe fed until she could eat on her own and had several veterinary visits to help us keep her healthy and understand what was happening to her eyes...she has vision in her left eye and not in her right and this does not slow her down in the least, we are not considering her to special needs at all since she has never known any different and is just like any other puppy.  When Wiley is old enough to be spayed, she will have her right eye removed at the same time and can come back to her foster family to have this done in April if her adopter wishes. This girl is active and playful, she loves her people and loves other dogs of all sizes and ages, she is working on house training, she has not met a cat and since she is active and curious, we believe she would do best with no cats (given she has one eye) 
Wiley has had 3 vaccinations/boosters and a DNA test done, she is Siberian  Husky, Labrador Retriever, Alaskan Malamute, chow chow and 37% herding breeds (shepherd, heeler)
if you would like to meet this miracle pup, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions

 An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Meet  Gumball! 

Gumball is a 4-6-year-old 72# Labrador retriever. He is a loving dog that is very obedient and only wants to please. He does great with older kids, 9-10 years old and over. He doesn’t much appreciate young children. 

He walks great on a leash and gets along well with all the dogs, cats and people he meets. 

He has been a country dog and may need some adjustment living in a more urban environment.

Interested in becoming a forever home for Gumball? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Gumball.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Gumball the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Astro is about 7 years old and was rescued from a shelter with a broken pelvis.  Fast forward a few months and Astro is ready for adoption.  He had his surgery and is completely healed.  He is a sweet boy who loves walks, attention and food.  He gets along with all dogs and just minds his own business.  He has completed his three weeks of obedience training.  Astro had selective hearing and didn’t always follow direction, kind of like a teenager.  He has now learned, sit, stay, come and all those other manners that dogs should have.  His hyper-active personality is now in check and he has mellowed with structure and direction that he learned in training.   Sounds like the perfect boy.  We aren’t sure but we think he is chi weenie with just enough of something else to give him a cute underbite  (he could use some braces).  I wish we knew every dog’s history and always wonder who they are and where they came from.  Something we will never know in Astro’s case.

If you are interested in adopting Astro please complete an application.

Https://dachshundsandfriends.org/adoption-application/

LOOKING FOR THE ADOPTION APPLICATION FORM? 
Please visit our website at: www.LHAR.dog 

If application is approved, pup will be held for you to meet/adopt within a few days of approval. 


(Appointment will be scheduled after application is approved) 

Location: WagsMore Adopt & Shop
                  450 Prospect Blvd, Frederick MD 21701
 
Age of pup: approx 5 years old as of January 2021
   
The adoption donation for Dudley is $375.00
This includes: Age appropriate vaccines and dewormings, rabies vaccine, HW prevention and neuter

Size:  medium 
Breed: Pittie/Hound mix is best guess?

Petfinder's Dog Size Recommendations:

Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

Please note our requirements to adopt a young puppy. 

1. Fill out our online application at: Www.LHAR.dog 

2. We require all current pets in the household to be up to date on shots and be spayed/neutered. Veterinary references will be contacted. 


His Story: 

LHAR rescued this sweet boy with the help of an organization in rural WV. Dudley is approx 5 years old and is ready to live his best life! He did not have the best of starts. His previous owners  left him outside on a chain without much human interaction. Now in a private LHAR foster home, Dudley has a HUGE appreciation for snuggles and couch time! He loves kids and playing with his toys. If you are looking for a loyal couch buddy, who loves to go for walks...Dudley is your man!

We have no confirmed history of Mom or Dad. We believe he is a pittie.hound mix.
  
He is  being fostered in a private home 

Weight: approx 50 lbs bs as of January 31st        
 
Photos were taken on January 31st     

Questions? Please email: lharinfo@gmail.com

Adoption donation fees: Please know that 100% of our fees go towards the rescue of puppies and dogs in need. Lonely Hearts Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non profit organization.

Thank you for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description: Panda is the cutest dog ever, but you cannot see how smushy her face is, in these photo! She is a year old and about 40 lbs of goofiness and mush. She is pushy and playful and bouncy and needs a bully breed experienced home. She loves humans and other dogs, and we can cat test. This petite girl is all wiggles and happiness. A must meet, for she will steal your heart for sure. (Fostered in PA - We do not text) (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there is clearly something wrong with your email!) Dog's Best Friend Adoption Center utilizes an adoption application and screening process. We require personal and vet references and a home check made prior to adopting one of our dogs. All of our dogs are companion animals that must be kept inside the house with the rest of the family members. All of our dogs are temperament tested, well mannered, and know some basic commands ~ they are worked with daily, as someone is always here with them. All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats. Adoption donations range from $250 to $450, depending on breed, age, size, vetting, and training of the dog (some pure bred and tiny dog fees are higher). This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care. Dog's Best Friend dogs truly make wonderful family pets. Please  email us for an application. (If you email us and do not hear back from us within 24 hours, please try again, as we most likely did not receive your email!) (Also note that many of our dogs are fostered just across the border into PA)

animal.description:
Panda is the cutest dog ever, but you cannot see how smushy her face is, in these photo! She is a year old and about 40 lbs of goofiness and mush. She is pushy and playful and bouncy and needs a bully breed experienced home. She loves humans and other dogs, and we can cat test. This petite girl is all wiggles and happiness. A must meet, for she will steal your heart for sure. CRPUPS@PTD.NET to contact us for any reason. (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there might be something wrong with your email! WE DO NOT TEXT) 
Lovable Mutts Adoption Center is a private, in home, all breed rescue/adoption facility, specializing in all ages and sizes of dogs.  We exist only on the kindness of your donations and adoptions!  We pride ourselves on being an HOLISTIC center and feed only holistic grain free foods and give daily, various, vitamins and supplements to all of our dogs. 

Our dogs are well socialized, very friendly, well mannered, affectionate, and in wonderful health. While some might be timid or shy, we work with our adopters in any way we can, to help them to work with their new family member. We give training tips and behavioral tips and even board for a very reasonable fee. Our dogs are extremely well cared for - most even know how to use a dog door by the time they leave us, know basic commands, and are crate trained!  We stand by our pups/dogs, and give 10 days for a refund and almost always take our dogs back at any age of their lives (can sometimes depend on the dog)! 

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center has an application screening process.  All applicants are asked to provide vet references, personal references, and a home visit.  We pride ourselves in matching up the right dog with the right home.  Sometimes this happens quickly and sometimes it might take awhile.  We hope you understand and are willing to wait for the perfect pup for your situation. We reserve the right to turn applicants down and to change our mind about a suitable match, for we are only concerned about what is best for our dogs.  Also note that we arrange our visiting hours around your schedule, as this is a private, in home facility.  We respond to all inquiries promptly, so if you have any trouble sending us an email, or have not heard back from us within 24 hours, please, CONTACT US AGAIN and check your spam!  (We all know how emails can be at times!)

Our dogs are spayed or neutered (if old enough), up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested, and free of fleas and ticks.  We temperament test our  dogs and they are all suitable for many family situations. Our dogs are well mannered,  and are in our family/home situation at this time (not kept in kennels or crates), and are worked with daily.  All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats, and we can cat test. Adoption donations vary with age, breed, vetting, and training of the dog, and range from $250 to $500. This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care.  (We do not tend to place puppies or small dogs with kids under 6 and reserve the right to match who WE feel would be the best homes for our dogs.)  
Please, come adopt one of our Lovable Mutts - you will be so glad you did!

(IF YOU DO NOT GET A REPLY EMAIL WITHIN 24 HOURS, CHECK YOUR SPAM BOX - WE REPLY EVERY FEW HOURS TO EMAILS)

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Mimi came to us from our friends at the wonderful Rescue Network. She was one of about a dozen dogs removed from a rural property when the owner was found deceased. Our shelter took in four of them. Mimi appears to be a beagle mix of some kind but don't hold us to that. She is delightfully chunky and has a wonderful personality. Mimi is very shy to start but loves a good belly rub on her substantial tummy. She's obviously had puppies in the past. Mimi will need to be spayed and her fee is $125.

The good stuff: Mimi is a sweetheart and does appear to love people and attention. She keeps her kennel very clean at the shelter.

The not so good stuff: Mimi is a very shy dog. She has received little to no basic training. She had never experienced a collar or leash before rescue. She will need a lot of patience and training when it comes to this.

We do think that Mimi would be fine with other dogs but don't know about cats. She does require a securely fenced area. NO underground fencing. She would do best in an adult only home or one with kids 5 and up.

NOTE: We are doing adoptions via private appointment only once an application has been completed and approved. Applications can be submitted right at our website, mchs.rescuegroups.org.

We are located at 101 22nd St. SE in Austin, right next to the airport. It's exit 180B off of I-90, right off of 218 South.

We do require that potential adopters be at least 21 years old and that any resident dogs be up to date on vaccinations, heartworm testing/preventative, and spayed or neutered.

animal.description:
Meet  Lavender! 

Lavender is a 2 to 3-year-old silky terrier/yorkie mix. She’s a little bit shy at first but very very sweet. She is working on her leash training and house training and doing very well.  She had blood work and dental done. 

Lavender was out of time when FWFP stepped in. 

Interested in becoming a forever home for Lavender? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Lavender.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Lavender the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Scroll down to learn more about this pet:

***
Bichon and Little Buddies is open only

by appointment with a completed application.
Dogs in foster homes require an appointment and approved application to meet. The application is online at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog If a dog is listed as available, then we are still taking applications - no need to email or call to ask about the status. Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Mystic

Breed: Mixed - Possibly Golden Retriever or German Shepherd

Approximate Age: 1 yr

Gender: Female

Weight: 40 lb

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Texas Transfer

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Mystic is a very sweet girl who came all the way from Texas in a snowstorm to find a wonderful home. Right now she seems to get a little overwhelmed if too many people are paying attention to her at the same time, and seems like she may prefer women to men - but she has been with us a very short time so she may get a little more relaxed with that as she adjusts to her new situation at the shelter. We do not have any other history or background, so do not know if she is housetrained or lived with other pets or with children. If interested in meeting Mystic, please fill out the preadoption application as that is the first step in adoption. If the dog is still listed on the adoptables pages, we are still taking applications.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. The application puts you under no obligation to adopt a dog from Bichon and Little Buddies.

The Dog Pre-Adoption Application can be found at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog

Thanks for thinking about adopting your new pet!More important information:

***We are a Wisconsin based rescue and do not ship our pets. If you are considering adoption you must be willing to drive to meet and adopt the pet, as well as bring the pet back to us if the adoption doesn't work. We adopt primarily in WI and IL, but will consider applicants in MN, IA, and MI.***

***Please do not set up an appointment to meet the animals until you are ready to take your pet home. If the meeting results in a match, you can often take the dog/cat home the same day or within a couple days if the medical care hasn't been completed. We are not able to hold pets for adopters beyond this time. Thanks for understanding.***

***While we hope all of our adoptions lead to permanent homes for the animals we place, sometimes things just don't work out. We do have a 30 day trial period. For the first 30 days, if you or Bichon and Little Buddies decide that the adoption isn't a good match for either the humans or the pet, the adoption fee will be refunded minus $50 within 30 days of the return of the dog. Bichon and Little Buddies also requires adopters to return the pet to us at any time that they are unable or unwilling to care for the animal anymore.***

***We do not show dogs/cats without an appointment. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog Please do not call/email until AFTER you have filled out an application.***

Bichon and Little Buddies is a State Licensed Rescue # 268555-DS

animal.description:
Meet  Angel (he is part of bonded pair)

Smoky and Angel are a bonded mother and son that came to us from a very bad situation. They are still very scared but improving after their two weeks in their new foster home. 

Angel is Smoky's son. He is 3 years old and about 20lbs.


Interested in becoming a forever home for Angel? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Angel.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Angel the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
*******WE ONLY ACCEPT APPLICATIONS WITHIN A 50 MILES RADIUS OF MURFREESBORO, TN******- (some exceptions but must be outstanding home for certain dogs)

Meet Sadie! She is a 7 yr old Red Tick Coon Hound looking for a forever home. She is move-in ready meaning housetrained and good with other dogs, cats, and kids. She does need to eat separately from everyone as she guards her food. She has a lot of energy and does need room to run and play but loves snuggles and lap time just as much. Fill out an adoption application if you would like to meet her!

Adoption fees are $250 for puppies and $200 for dogs over 8 months. If you think you would be interested, please complete our no obligation application and we can start the process at www.middletennesseetreasures.com.

Our dogs and cats are kept in foster homes with volunteers who share their homes with these animals until the right adoptive home is found. These foster homes evaluate for temperament and also work on basic training with the dogs. Our dogs and cats have been seen by a vet, brought up to date on vaccinations, micro-chipped, heartworm tested, cleared of parasites and spayed or neutered if 6 months or older. 

The first step in adopting from Middle Tennessee Treasures is to complete an adoption application.(http://www.middletennesseetreasures.com/adoption/) Vet references are usually called first. When we contact your vet we ask about current and past pets (both dogs and cats). We ask if all animals are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations, seen on a yearly basis and whether dogs are on heartworm preventative. Personal references are called and finally a home visit is set up. The purpose of the home visit to meet you, your family, and any pets you may have. It also allows us to see what kind of dog or cat would be the best fit for your home. 

This screening process helps to ensure that each rescued dog is placed in a loving, safe, and permanent home. We do not place our dogs on a first come, first serve basis, but according to the needs of the dog and family.

animal.description:
Meet Pearl!

***Please note Pearl is deaf and blind. 
And being fostered in Tehachapi, CA. But can be transported for an additional fee. ****

https://vm.tiktok.com/ZMe1Ythu3/

She came to us after her breeder dropped her off at the shelter overnight, while it was closed with her sister, Blossum. She is a Double Merle  Australian Shepherd, and unfortunately is blind and deaf. But, that does not stop her from being a fun loving puppy, who can live a normal life. She get's around just find, sniffing the air, and the ground to find her way, she loves to play, is fearless, and is so special. She is very adored here, and with the right family, she is going to make someone such a fun addition to their home. We do not fear that her special needs is going to effect her being able to live a full happy life, she will just need a bit more help than a dog that can see and hear. 

She is currently working on crate training and doing excellent. She sleeps soundly, and rarely rarely has an accident in her crate. She loves to tug on the bottom of your pants, and be such a little goofball. 

If you are interested in adopting Pearl, please head to our website FIRST to fill out an application. We will also be asking for photo's of home, to ensure Pearls safety, so have that ready. 

Pearl is too young to be spayed, so adopters will sign a contract stating that it's their responsibly to get it done after the dog turns 6 months old, but before 1 years old.
