animal.description:
Scroll down to learn more about this pet:

***
Bichon and Little Buddies is open only

by appointment with a completed application.
Dogs in foster homes require an appointment and approved application to meet. The application is online at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog If a dog is listed as available, then we are still taking applications - no need to email or call to ask about the status. Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Taz

Breed: Chihuahua (or mix)

Approximate Age: 2 yr

Gender: Male

Weight: 12 lb

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Texas Transfer

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Taz came to us all the way from Texas in a snowstorm because he wanted to find a loving home. He was found as a stray in Texas with all his canine teeth filed or wore down. He is a friendly guy and we were told he was good with other dogs. We do not have any other history or background, so do not know if he is housetrained or lived with other pets or with children. If interested in meeting Taz, please fill out the preadoption application as that is the first step in adoption. If the dog is still listed on the adoptables pages, we are still taking applications.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. The application puts you under no obligation to adopt a dog from Bichon and Little Buddies.

The Dog Pre-Adoption Application can be found at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog

Thanks for thinking about adopting your new pet!More important information:

***We are a Wisconsin based rescue and do not ship our pets. If you are considering adoption you must be willing to drive to meet and adopt the pet, as well as bring the pet back to us if the adoption doesn't work. We adopt primarily in WI and IL, but will consider applicants in MN, IA, and MI.***

***Please do not set up an appointment to meet the animals until you are ready to take your pet home. If the meeting results in a match, you can often take the dog/cat home the same day or within a couple days if the medical care hasn't been completed. We are not able to hold pets for adopters beyond this time. Thanks for understanding.***

***While we hope all of our adoptions lead to permanent homes for the animals we place, sometimes things just don't work out. We do have a 30 day trial period. For the first 30 days, if you or Bichon and Little Buddies decide that the adoption isn't a good match for either the humans or the pet, the adoption fee will be refunded minus $50 within 30 days of the return of the dog. Bichon and Little Buddies also requires adopters to return the pet to us at any time that they are unable or unwilling to care for the animal anymore.***

***We do not show dogs/cats without an appointment. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog Please do not call/email until AFTER you have filled out an application.***

Bichon and Little Buddies is a State Licensed Rescue # 268555-DS

animal.description:
Meet Blossum!
Being fostered in Tehachapi, CA

***Please note Blossum is mostly deaf and blind***

https://vm.tiktok.com/ZMe1Ythu3/

Blossum came to us after her breeder dumped her and her sister Pearl at the shelter overnight. She is a double merle Aussie, and is the funniest little thing!
She is blind in one eye, and we thought she was deaf, but it seems she may have partial hearing. Her special needs does not slow her down even a tad, she is super playful, bouncy, and get's around really well! She is fearless, and loves people. We do not think anything will hold her back from living a normal dog life, of course, with just a little bit more help. But not much! She is going to make someone such a special companion, with ton's of fun and laughter. 

She is currently working on crate training and doing excellent. She sleeps soundly, and rarely rarely has an accident in her crate. She loves to tug on the bottom of your pants, and be such a little goofball. 

If you are interested in adopting Blossum, please head to our website FIRST to fill out an application. We will also be asking for photo's of home, to ensure Blossums safety, so have that ready to send over also. 

Pearl is too young to be spayed, so adopters will sign a contract stating that it's their responsibly to get it done after the dog turns 6 months old, but before 1 years old.

She is located in Tehachapi, CA. 
But can be transported for an additional fee, if needed.

animal.description:
Haley is happy to begin the next chapter in her life, finding a forever home! This 6-year-old beauty came in because her family did not have enough time for her. Haley is always grinning, cheek to cheek! She is so full of love and knows she can shower her humans with lots of kisses! Haley loves to play and often gets the zoomies. But she is also never opposed to a nice cuddle session, belly rubs included of course! Haley will follow you around all day and when it is time to relax, she will happily lay at your feet. She is a 50-pound love who just truly enjoys the company of her humans. She is also extremely smart and already knows sit, shake, lie down, speak, and sit pretty! Haley may welcome calmer, medium to large dog siblings (pending a meet), and no cats or small animals. Haley is house broken and would welcome children of all ages. Could you hold the key to Haley's heart?! 

All of our dogs and puppies are spayed/neutered prior to being placed for adoption. They also receive a physical examination from our veterinarian and are tested for heartworm. All of our dogs receive age-appropriate vaccinations (including rabies) and they are treated for fleas. All cats and dogs adopted from our facility are microchipped. 

For more information, please call (440) 951-6122, email adopt@lakehumane.org or visit our website at www.lakehumane.org. Thank you for choosing adoption!

animal.description: Meet Boss! Boss is a 2 year old, American Bulldog and Staffordshire Terrier mix. Boss is a hunk. He is a little over 70 lbs and all muscle. With that being said, he is also the sweetest soul. He is dog friendly but is dominant so will need a more submissive dog (and more dogs his size) in the home and we will require a meet and greet. We will say no to cats, although he doesn't immediately go after them he seems to have some interest in them. Boss is going to make someone a great companion as he is so smart and his mannerisms are exquisite. Boss is updated on vaccines, dewormer, has his rabies shot and is scheduled for neuter surgery. He will also be microchipped. $125 to adopt. - Interested? Apply online! http://www.hshcwv.org/wanting-to-adopt.html If you don't apply for this guy you are missing out!

animal.description:
Bear with us as we boast about how wonderful this pup is! Bear is a 4-year-old Shepherd who came to Lake Humane Society because her owner lost their home. And we can attest that she is one lovable teddy bear! Bear wants nothing more than a family to love and a warm fire place to snuggle up by. Bear came in with and old hind leg fracture that could not be repaired, and therefore it did need amputated. She has been recovering in a foster home and is now getting used to her new way of life, and ready to take the next step...finding a forever home! 

Bear has a gentle and kind demeanor, and she loves every human she meets. She would prefer to be the only animal in the home to assure she never misses out on getting love and cuddles. Bear is a strong girl who is conquering the challenge of being on 3-legs, and she is doing great. Although, she may do best in a home with limited stairs and challenges around the house. Could you be the one to give Bear the home she truly deserves?! 

All of our dogs and puppies are spayed/neutered prior to being placed for adoption. They also receive a physical examination from our veterinarian and are tested for heartworm. All of our dogs receive age-appropriate vaccinations (including rabies) and they are treated for fleas. All cats and dogs adopted from our facility are microchipped. 

For more information, please call (440) 951-6122, email adopt@lakehumane.org or visit our website at www.lakehumane.org. Thank you for choosing adoption!

animal.description:
www.huskyrescueteam.org

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.org**Do not apply if you don't meet the criteria listed here**

We are now accepting applications for the Solar Siblings. They will be ready to go home with their new families 2/21, when they turn 8 weeks old!

NOTE.... this is a 15 year commitment, so do not take this lightly!! The puppies are Siberian Husky / German Shepherd mixes. To be eligible to adopt, you must have breed experience with at least one of these breeds. Their adoption area is within driving distance to our vet in Davidsonville, MD, where they will be spayed and neutered late June.... NO EXCEPTIONS!!

They need homes who have other young, playful dogs and families who will not leave them for long periods of time. No small animals, small children or apartments. Remember, puppies are susceptible to disease, until they are fully vaccinated at 4 months of age. You must have a plan to keep them safe until they're fully vaccinated. If you are interested and can provide the type of home they need, you can apply on our website. We will not respond to your application if you do not meet the criteria above. We will be matching puppies to families based on their personality.

www.huskyrescueteam.org

~~Husky Education And Rescue Team is a foster based rescue. Our dogs are in our foster homes all up and down the east coast. We do not have a facility in which you can visit. We find this a huge benefit because we learn our dogs and are able to educate our adopters on what it's like to have them live in your home. Part of our process, once pre-approved, is to speak with the foster for the dog you're interested in. If you're still interested in adopting from our rescue the first step is to complete our adoption application online at www.huskyrescueteam.org/apply

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.org

animal.description: Hi! My name is Chispi! I was rescued in Puerto Rico before arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. I am super sweet and would just love to join your family! I like to play with other small dogs, like myself, and I think that I could be very happy entering a family with younger children. animal.description: Hi! My name is Sarge! I was rescued in Georgia along with my sister, prior to arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. I am a beautiful, big brindle boy and I am totally a lover, despite being hurt by humans early in my life. I came in with a pretty bad burn on my back, but the wonderful people here on the ranch have been treating me and things are healing just fine. I would prefer to be the king of the castle in my new home and not reside with any other dogs. I don't usually like to play with other dogs and it's not uncommon to find me off by myself, as I seem to enjoy my space from time to time. I think I'd be happiest in a home that has a great big yard for me to run around and play in, when I want to. I could use a little bit of work on my manners, but I'm definitely worth it. I do seem to have mostly mastered potty-training, and I love to go on long-leashed walks with anyone who will take me. I was living in a foster home with lots of other dogs and we all got along just fine! I am not a huge fan of cats so living in a feline-free home would be preferably. I think I would also do best in an adult-only home, since I can be a little bit mouthy and tend to jump when I'm excited.

Meet Faith!
*Will be ready to leave to their new homes after FEB 13TH* 

She is one of 6 puppies that came in with their momma Harriet. They are a Beagle (hound type) mix. Very sweet, loving puppies. We do not expect them to be over 50lbs. Beagle's are known for their independent nature, always using their noses, can be difficult to train in some aspects, and can be rather noisey. Please do your research before applying. Although, a more difficult breed, they are very loving with their families, get along well with other animals, food driven, and be goofballs! 

If you interesting in adopting the FIRST step is to head to our website and fill out an application. Please be aware that we will ask for photos of your home, where the dog being adopt will spend most it's time, and have these ready to send, if approved. 

These puppies are too young to be spayed/nuetered and will go to their homes on a contract stating they must have the surgery done after 6 months old, but before 1 years old.

animal.description:
Hi and thank you for your interest in adopting from The Foster Farm!

COVID-19 UPDATE: Due to the overwhelming amount of applications, calls, and emails regarding our currently available pets, we cannot respond to everyone at this time. We appreciate your enthusiasm to rescue a new family member, but please be aware that we simply do not have enough pets in foster care to meet demands at this time. 

WE ARE NOT DOING OUT-OF-STATE ADOPTIONS AT THIS TIME.

In order to help us process your application, please include as much detail and information as possible. Our adoption process is not first come first serve - we work extremely hard to meet the needs of every pet individually, and we do not base our matches on appearances (color, coat length, etc.). 

If you're inquiring about our adoption process, please visit thefosterfarm.org/adopt for information, policies, and procedures. 

If you have submitted an application at thefosterfarm.org/adopt and received the confirmation email from Cognito Forms (your receipt will appear as a copy of the application you submitted), we are reviewing your application. If you are approved to adopt, you will receive an email approval within 72 business hours (Monday through Friday only)! Because our organization is run entirely by four volunteers each with full-time jobs, families, personal pets, and foster animals, we are only able to reach out to approved applicants. 

Thank you so much for your patience and understanding as we all navigate these exceptional circumstances together!

Stay healthy and safe!
The Foster Farm Team

Abigayle is the perfect companion dog - she loves attention and affection and will return the favor. She loves to be with her person and is a happy-go-lucky little girl. She gets along fine with other dogs and pays no attention to the cat in her foster home. She's very friendly and will make a nice companion for some lucky person or people.

Abigayle is a Dachshund mix gal who is 6-7 years old and weighs 13 pounds.

Abi is quite the athlete! She can climb wire crates and chain link fencing, so she should be walked on a leash (although she could use more work on leash walking) unless her new home has a wooden fence which she can't climb. She has progressed pretty well with pottying outside as long as she knows what is expected of her. She does fine in a crate but prefers to not be crated.

If you are interested in making this gal your new BFF, please fill out an application at www.northstarpets.org & be sure to ask for ABIGAYLE TX!

animal.description:
Hey everyone, my name is Belle!! Upon intake into the shelter I had major trauma to my face. It is all healed up now but as you can see I have an adorable crooked smile, but I don't mind! I can be a little shy at first but I truly love people and am definitely a velcro baby!! I also love kids, other dogs, and I like cats too... although I don't think the one I live with currently likes me much so I hide when he's mad. 

I love my people so much I just follow my foster mom around everywhere. If I could live in someones lap all day every day I would be so happy!!! I am very eager to please. All I want is to make my humans happy! I can be nervous in new situations but I just look at my foster mom. If she says it's okay then I trust her and get more comfortable!

I know my name, have a great off leash recall, I also walk great on a leash and am very gentle and calm. I also know sit, wait, leave it, up ( to stand on my hind legs), load up, and go (to chase the tennis ball). We also have been working on my general anxiety and crate training. At first I was so scared of those crates but I have a come a long way now!!

I would love to meet you if you think I would be a good fit for you and your family!! If you would like to meet me in real life please fill out an application!!

animal.description:
Meet  Duke! 

Duke is a 1 to 2-year-old Labrador retriever and golden retriever mix. He is a very very sweet boy who does well on a leash with little pulling.  He is learning sit, kennel/crate trained and is doing very well at being housetrained. 

He’s a very happy boy that just wants to please. He is 63 pounds of love and wags 

Duke was out of time when FWFP stepped in. 

Interested in becoming a forever home for Duke? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Duke.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Duke the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.This good boy wants a home more than you could ever imagine. And he is a GOOD boy, too. He is going to make a wonderful family dog/best friend. So young still that he is barely out of puppyhood. That makes him ready to learn what you want him to know. He is very smart, so if you show him what you want, he will do his very best to do it for you. He so much wants to be loved. His temperament is friendly and from his shepherd side he gets exceptional loyalty. He has never had a chance to give his heart away...you will be his first and his forever. He has had all his shots and been completely vetted. All he needs now is you. He is waiting patiently. Note from his foster: Tom is currently working with a trainer and the new adopter will need to continue with this after adoption. He is going to need a big backyard with a fence that is at least 6 ft high where he can run and play safely. A more rural area would be better for our boy, rather than urban. He is frightened of cars and trucks going by as he is walked. No children under the age of 12 in the home, since he can be a bit nippy and mouthy while playing. Tom is working hard with his trainer, so he will be ready for his forever home.
If you are interested in Tom, please fill out an application at:
https://reachoutrescue.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=4588 Or contact:
rorrcanine@gmail.com
*** Click here to sponsor this dog! ***

animal.description:
Hi potential human! My name is Ollie and I am looking for a forever home. I am a very chill dog and if I could, I would be at my human's side 24/7. I love to lay around and I take A LOT of naps but in my forever home I would prefer to nap while cuddling because who doesn't want to cuddle? Even though cuddling is my number 1 priority I also love taking walks and smelling everything I come across. I like to play with my toys and am pretty good at fetch. Sometimes I trick my human and act like I'm going to bring the ball back but just run around with it instead. I like to play with other dogs but would need to meet your dog first to make sure we like each other! 



I have met 2 super cute little humans who were around 5 years old. I really liked them but sometimes their quick-moving toys scared me a little bit. Because I like to cuddle so much I don't like being away from my family. Whatever family adopts me will have to know that I get really sad when my people leave and they will have to work with me and teach me that they will always come back and that it is okay to be alone sometimes.



If you might be the family for me email foster@kcpetproject.org to meet me!

animal.description:
Are you a sucker for hound dog ears and puppy kisses? Look no further than Miller! This little chunk is a total goofball puppy with big paws and a big personality! He was born in December 2020 and is ready for his forever home. We aren’t sure of his exact mix but expect him to be a large dog when full grown. 

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for puppies covers initial deworming,  puppy vaccinations, microchip, and spay/neuter at the rescue's approved vet at 6 months of age. Please see our website for more information.  

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Looking to melt into your heart and onto your couch!
I require someone to go slow with me, as I can be a little shy at first.After a chance to take my time and feel comfortable, I will be your side-kick forever!I love walks, though loud noises do startle me. I don't pull on leash and stay right next to whoever is walking me.I scratch at the door or whine when I need to go potty, but otherwise I am content to lay on the couch and sleep most of the day.I am mostly quiet in the crate, but will cry if I need to go outside. I sleep through the night in a crate and won't wake you up.I love hot dogs and cheese!Sometimes I get bursts of energy and do jump up on people, but most of the time I'm calm.I am endearingly known as Garfield Dogbecause my personality is so similar to him.In a shelter setting, I have been noted to jump very high (approx 6-7ft)and escape an open top kennel,so I should not be left in a yard unattended and high fences are a plus. I have not tried to escape a yard while with my foster mom. I lived with children in my previous home and did well with them. I'd do well with other dogs with slow introductions.

General Socialization Notes:

 I am a bit shy, at first, but will warm up. I would do well in a home with another dog as long as we can do slow introductions. Some dogs can be intimidating to me. Sometimes in scary situations, I will growl and have snapped when I was scared.

Does Godiva like other pets?

 I have previously lived with cats, chickens and dogs. I was reported to do well withthe cats and chickens. I have chased squirrels and rabbitsoutside and that is usually the only time I pull on leash.I may not get along with all dogs as they intimidate me sometimes,but I have been doing well in my foster home with another medium sized dog. I alsoplayed well with one of the dogs from my previous home. Because I love food, I should be fed separately from other animals so we can all enjoy our meals in peace. A slow introduction to another dog would be best to set me up for the greatest success.

Does Godiva like children?

 I have previously lived with children from1 year old to14 years oldand did well with them and would often cuddle and sleep near them.

Favorite Toys:

 Sometimes I will play fetch and I love to chew on bones. Overall, I'm not that interested in toys.

Ideal Forever Home:

 My ideal forever home is someone that is home often to snuggle and take me on walks. I would love a nice bed or couch to cuddle on.A calm household that allows me to get as much sleep as I want is also a plus! I'd do okay with calmchildren and I could be an only dog or get along with another dog, as long as we can do slow introductions.

animal.description:
We are looking for just the right home for Zeus.  Many of the volunteers at the shelter where he has lived much of his life totally adore him.  Everyone is rooting for him.  We are fostering him in our home currently and so know him extremely well.  The good news:  Zeus is a beautiful, loving, playful dog who is extremely loyal and devoted to “his person”.  He will follow you around and want to be wherever you are.  He loves to lie at your feet while you’re on the computer or beside you while you’re watching tv.  He’s just dying to play sometimes and is really funny when he gets going.  He gets along with any dog we’ve put him with (currently he living with four other dogs).  No problems at all.   He is great on walks in terms of ignoring other dogs and people and really just loves “sniffing” along.  He does pull hard, but that could be trained.  He is about 43 pounds and is about 4 ½ years old.  He doesn’t chew things up or destroy things.  Almost a perfect dog.  
However, Zeus will need an experienced owner in a quiet household in order to become the dog he can be.  While almost perfect, he is very afraid of strangers (coming into the home – not on walks) and, at this point, will not warm to anyone for a couple of days.  He will bark at them and sound pretty scary.  He has never bitten anyone at all – just looks and sounds scary.  We are working on training him to accept strangers into his home, but this will be a process that needs to be continued.   
So, a beautiful terrific dog who needs just the right home.  If you are interested, please feel free to call us or email us to obtain other information and, perhaps, to meet him.
animal.name: Zeus

animal.description:
Hello world, I'm Ziggy Stardust!

When I came to the shelter I weighed just over three pounds, and I was severely malnourished for a 4-month-old puppy. I had been found curled up against a tire in the Michigan winter snow. As soon as the staff brought me a little food, I gobbled it right up, trying to stand, but it was hard. Every time they would talk to me, I wagged my tail just as much as I could. They knew, "This girl wants to live!" So, they warmed me up, got some fluids in me, and found me a super wonderful foster mom with a dog to help me get out of the woods.
I have been fostered for just over three weeks. I have doubled my weight in that time and am getting stronger everyday! My foster mom wants my new family to know, "Stardust is a very sweet and spunky puppy full of energy and life. She is social and curious and loves to meet everyone, humans and animals alike. She would do best in a home with someone who is willing to spend the time teaching her manners, as she is still working on potty training and basic obedience."

I am ready to live the best life a puppy can live with my furever family! As David Bowie once said, "I don't know where I'm going from here, but I promise it won't be boring."
animal.name: Ziggy Stardust

animal.description:
Meet Malcolm! This sweet boy is being fostered in Millis MA. He is a chill love-lump of a puppy learning how to "dog" since his arrival from Mississippi. He willl need the training + exercise like all puppies do. 

Read through our adoption process and other adoption FAQs here www.rescueinc.dog/FAQs

All of our pups come with the following: 


	Spayed or Neutered
	Age appropriate vaccinations + dewormed + 4DX test (if older than 6 months)
	New martingale collar with 6' lead + temp ID tag
	30 days free insurance to be activated within 24 hours of your wellness visit with your veterinarian
	Microchip with free registration for your new pup, but also for any other pets in your household too!
	Southern pups, younger than 6 months, come with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm prevention to prevent any lapse of protection 
	Our southern dogs, 6 months and older, come with a **Proheart 6 injection which provides 6 months of Heartworm protection (approx value of $100) + dose of flea / tick preventative


**dogs surrendered to us in MA do not recieve the Proheart 6 injection but do go home with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm preventative so there is no lapse in protection

Ages listed can be approximate and breed mixes are a best guess based on physical characteristics. 

If you are seeing this listing on Petfinder, please apply through the link on our website at www.rescueinc.dog/adopt 

Please do not email with questions or message through Petfinder. Communication with the rescue always starts with submitting an application. 

If you see this listing, the pup is still available. We pull listings after 2 to 3 viable applications are submitted.

animal.description:
*Please read Zorro's full bio to ensure that you are a good match for him.

Meet Zorro, a 3-year-old, 20 lb Chihuahua and Dachshund blend boy (a Chiweenie). He has not had the best life - he came from a hoarding situation and was just not treated very well by his previous owner. He will need a very patient, dog-savvy adopter willing to put the time in with treats and snuggles and walks to let him know that he is safe and loved. He is great with cats, and also is house trained (needs to have a schedule) and crate trained, though he does love sleeping in the bed with his foster momma. He is very skittish and scared of strangers and takes quite a while to open up and start trusting but once he does, he will be a great sidekick. This boy can't seem to shake his previous life completely and has a fear of men - A MUST-HAVE for him is a home with only women (or limited contact with men). For this reason, he also needs an ADULT-ONLY home with no children. He immediately finds his safe place (often a corner of the couch) until he feels more confident moving about the house and following his momma around. Zorro is starved for human touch and has learned to give high fives and nose kisses to ensure you keep petting him. He may be best as the only dog in the home, or only having a laid back, calm sibling who doesn't try to force playtime.

If you want to show this sweet boy that not all people are bad and give him the love that he deserves and learn more about him from his foster mom, please visit our website www.PoodleandPoochRescue.org where you will find the application to adopt. He is up to date on his vaccines, neutered, heartworm negative, and microchipped. His adoption donation is $250.

animal.description:
Moxie is sweet and silly 4yr old Rottweiler in need of a loving home. She loves belly rubs and biscuits. She does NOT like water (rain, puddles, beach...) but she will stand still outside to get a bath through the garden hoes.

She loves people and kids. She could possible knock over small children (1-4yrs) only due to her size. She if doesn't like a human, you shouldn't either.

She currently lives with other large dogs and she gets along wonderfully with 3 out of the 4.

MOXIE CANNOT BE AROUND CATS! Or small dogs, rodents, birds ect. As she has a high prey drive. She will try to chase them outside, along with cars driving too fast, buses, garbage trucks and anything with a Diesel engine (she doesn't like the sound) so she needs a fenced in yard and adopter will need to be mindful of this when walking her should sh encounter this. She howls when she's excited or there are sirens and is not a fan of fireworks.

This good girl is crate trained and house trained. She has a crate with a Velcro cover that would go with her.

animal.description: Reggie is such a great dog. Very clingy and loyal, as most all GSD's are. He has clearly had a terrible life recently, for he is all bones, which has weakened him, but he is getting stronger daily and is more active and playful. He is also hw+ and is on slow-kill treatment, which means he stays on his once a month medicine, for several months to come, til he is hw free. He is good with people and dogs, and might love to be a second dog in a home. Prefer he not be with really young kids, for that might be too much for him, although he is very gentle. Reggie is so smart and so handsome in person. This 6 year old boy is skin and bones, and only weighs about 63 lbs right now - he should weight at least 80. We prefer a home with GSD experience and a fenced yard. Please, open your hearts and homes to this awesome boy, for you will be so glad you did. (Fostered in PA - We do not text) (If you do not hear back from us within about 6 hours, send us your phone number, for there is clearly something wrong with your email!) Dog's Best Friend Adoption Center utilizes an adoption application and screening process. We require personal and vet references and a home check made prior to adopting one of our dogs. All of our dogs are companion animals that must be kept inside the house with the rest of the family members. All of our dogs are temperament tested, well mannered, and know some basic commands ~ they are worked with daily, as someone is always here with them. All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats. Adoption donations range from $250 to $450, depending on breed, age, size, vetting, and training of the dog (some pure bred and tiny dog fees are higher). This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care. Dog's Best Friend dogs truly make wonderful family pets. Please  email us for an application. (If you email us and do not hear back from us within 24 hours, please try again, as we most likely did not receive your email!) (Also note that many of our dogs are fostered just across the border into PA)

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center is a private, in home, all breed rescue/adoption facility, specializing in all ages and sizes of dogs.  We exist only on the kindness of your donations and adoptions!  We pride ourselves on being an HOLISTIC center and feed only holistic grain free foods and give daily, various, vitamins and supplements to all of our dogs. 

Our dogs are well socialized, very friendly, well mannered, affectionate, and in wonderful health. While some might be timid or shy, we work with our adopters in any way we can, to help them to work with their new family member. We give training tips and behavioral tips and even board for a very reasonable fee. Our dogs are extremely well cared for - most even know how to use a dog door by the time they leave us, know basic commands, and are crate trained!  We stand by our pups/dogs, and give 10 days for a refund and almost always take our dogs back at any age of their lives (can sometimes depend on the dog)! 

Lovable Mutts Adoption Center has an application screening process.  All applicants are asked to provide vet references, personal references, and a home visit.  We pride ourselves in matching up the right dog with the right home.  Sometimes this happens quickly and sometimes it might take awhile.  We hope you understand and are willing to wait for the perfect pup for your situation. We reserve the right to turn applicants down and to change our mind about a suitable match, for we are only concerned about what is best for our dogs.  Also note that we arrange our visiting hours around your schedule, as this is a private, in home facility.  We respond to all inquiries promptly, so if you have any trouble sending us an email, or have not heard back from us within 24 hours, please, CONTACT US AGAIN and check your spam!  (We all know how emails can be at times!)

Our dogs are spayed or neutered (if old enough), up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested, and free of fleas and ticks.  We temperament test our  dogs and they are all suitable for many family situations. Our dogs are well mannered,  and are in our family/home situation at this time (not kept in kennels or crates), and are worked with daily.  All of our dogs do well with other dogs and many do well with cats, and we can cat test. Adoption donations vary with age, breed, vetting, and training of the dog, and range from $250 to $500. This donation helps to pay for shots, de-wormings, spays, neuters, flea protection, heartworm/Lyme testing, treatments, and other vetting/issues that might be needed, for dogs in our care.  (We do not tend to place puppies or small dogs with kids under 6 and reserve the right to match who WE feel would be the best homes for our dogs.)  
Please, come adopt one of our Lovable Mutts - you will be so glad you did!

(IF YOU DO NOT GET A REPLY EMAIL WITHIN 24 HOURS, CHECK YOUR SPAM BOX - WE REPLY EVERY FEW HOURS TO EMAILS)

animal.description:
Samson has captured our hearts and mainly because of his struggles to get where he is today…with HAIR!  Samson is an 8 year old love bug and it is his time to shine with a new family.  He was surrendered to the shelter by his owner who couldn’t afford to sort out his medical issue. He was well loved for sure and you can tell by his fabulous demeanor.  This guy loves everyone and gets along with both his foster’s other dogs and cat.  What a guy!  Since Samson has been in our rescue program, we have given him consistent medical care which involves tests and different types of medicines. In complete full disclosure, we think we have enough medical diagnosis and a treatment plan that he can now go his forever home.  We discovered that he has a thyroid issue which is now managed by medicine.  We are thrilled by his progress and look how his hair is growing back in!  What a handsome boy he will be soon. Due to the fact that he probably will need to have his medicine for his remaining days, we would hope that his new adoptive home have the financial means to keep up with what he might need medically.  Our rescue has figured so much out already so we are hopeful consistent monthly maintenance will be all that is required. If you truly have a rescue heart and want a lovely fur baby, EMAIL STORKWOODS@COMCAST.NET for an adoption application. We hope he captures your heart as he has ours!

Samson is being fostered in Middle TN. We have foster homes in several areas of the country.

Foster Homes Needed!

Do you have time and room in your life for a foster dog?

http://www.muttloverescue.org/foster.html

*****************

Lovie was found at a Louisiana rest stop and taken to the shelter. She weighs about 20 pounds and is estimated to be about 10 years old. She is currently undergoing heartworm treatment and would welcome a foster or permanent home.

**BECAUSE OF OUR REQUIREMENT FOR A HOME VISIT, WE ARE ONLY ABLE TO ADOPT TO HOMES IN THE NORTHERN VA / MARYLAND / DC METRO AREA**

We have adoption events EVERY SATURDAY from 12-3 p.m. Please note that not all dogs can attend every event, so if you are interested in meeting a particular dog, please complete a no-obligation application on our website at http://www.muttloverescue.org/application.html OR write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

Upcoming adoption events:

Mutt Love Rescue is doing everything we can to ensure the health and safety of our volunteers and adopters while continuing our mission to find homes for as many dogs as possible.

Effective immediately, we will not be holding our weekly adoption events. Dogs available for adoption can be met by appointment only. Potential adopters should submit an online application at http://muttloverescue.org/application.html. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to let you know the next steps.

We are always desperate for foster homes, now more than ever. If you are interested in fostering during this difficult time, please complete an application... unless you are a previous adopter/foster, then you can just contact us via phone (703-988-2608) or email (adopt@muttloverescue.org) to tell us which dog you want to foster!

For information on sponsoring this dog, please write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

WE NEED FOSTER HOMES! FOR MORE INFORMATION, PLEASE EMAIL ADOPT@MUTTLOVERESCUE.ORG.

Visit us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/muttloverescue
Follow us on Twitter: @Muttlove_Rescue

animal.description:
Sally is available for adoption to Texas residents only.

Sally is a young adult who has a sweet personality. She is timid, and not had a lot of human interaction, but absolutely doesn't want to leave your side once you earn her trust. She appears to have had at least one litter of puppies. Sally was picked up as a stray and was terrified in the shelter. She has blossomed into a calm, loving girl who is content to just hang out wherever you are. 

Sally would probably do best with older children at least 7 or older. She has not shown any aggression to children, but since she is a bit timid we think younger children may be too much for her. When adopted, Sally will need a few days or longer to acclimate to her new surroundings. She still cowers like she may have been abused when you approach her. 

If you are interested in applying for adoption, please copy and paste this link into your browser.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1zGtCUUqOvBHxQtIy7j4-qA_W-b_PIitAaDXAf8MuKHg/edit

animal.description:
We would like to introduce you to Gem.
This puppy is so sweet and promises to be a good girl for her family. We like to remind people that puppies are more than a cute face, they require time and lots of patience. If you are not up for housbreaking and crate training a puppy is not for you. Gem is hoping to find a family that will take her on walks, take her camping and give her lots of kisses. She would love to have a fenced yard to chase squirrels and bask in the sun but that is not a deal breaker. 
If you want to be considered for Gem please go to www.newhopepetrescue.com for an application.


Please check out our adoption process & on-line application here: https://www.newhopepetrescue.com/

Adoption Fee for dogs cover the following vetting:

1. UTD on shots (age appropriate)
2. Wormed
3. HW tested (over 1 year old)
4. Micro-chipped
5. Spayed/neutered

Adoption Fee for cats cover the following vetting:

1. UTD on shots (age appropriate)
2. Wormed
3. Felv/FIV Combo Test (as appropriate)
4. Micro-chipped
5. Spayed/neutered

animal.description: J.R. is an adorable 5 month old Coonhound x Lab mix who recently joined our program. Not only is this boy cute as can be, but he’s sweet as sugar. J.R. gets along with other dogs and is best suited for a home where he has a canine friend – for this reason, we will not consider applications for him unless there is another dog in the family. True to his breed, J.R. LOVES all of the amazing smells that walks have to offer and is a pretty “nose-to-the-ground” kind of boy. He thinks that cookies are the best, is good in the car and loves to meet new people. J.R. is looking for an active family who will be dedicated to taking him to positive reinforcement training classes for skill development and as a way to keep his little brain working and stimulated. This cutie would be fine in a home with kids 12 and over. Cats are unknown. For more information on this bundle of fun, email info@thedogrescuersinc.ca

animal.description:
This sweet old man in Jensen! He came to us from a shelter partner in Cleveland, and we think he is a boxer/pit bull mix. Jensen told us that he's happy to be in Pittsburgh because he's secretly been a Steelers fan all his life! Jensen is a big old guy, at 79 lbs and 7 years old, but this guy has so much life!

Jensen was found as a stray, so we don't know much about his past. However his previous shelter notes that he is house-broken! In shelter play groups, Jensen has shown that he's totally fine with dogs who are similarly chill and relaxed. He enjoys toys and food games, and would love to spend his golden years hanging out with you. Just like any other old guy, he has some worn teeth and some lumps. But our vet team has checked Jensen all over and thinks that he will blossom in the home. Apply for Jensen today!

Thank you for your interest in our adoptable animals! Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, we do require appointments to see our adoptable animals. Please complete the adoption application and a Customer Care Associate will be in contact with you. PLEASE NOTE: We ask that when you submit your application, that you are available to schedule an appointment within the next 24-48 hours.

animal.description:
**PLEASE ENSURE YOU READ THIS BIO TO THE END - IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING YOU WILL FIND INFO ON HOW TO DO SO IN THIS BIO. AS LONG AS THIS DOG IS STILL POSTED, WE ARE STILL ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR HER SO NO NEED TO EMAIL ASKING IF SHE'S AVAILABLE, WE WILL REMOVE THE LISTING WHEN APPLICATIONS ARE CLOSED.**

Amy is a 3 month old husky mix who came to Precious Paws Rescue from a  community in northern Manitoba. She is an active and playful girl who is now fully vetted and ready to find her adoptive home!

Amy is house trained, crate trained and she knows "Sit". She is working on her leash training and she is getting really good at it! Amy is also working on calming down and not nipping so she will need a family who is ready to continue her training for that. When going for car rides, Amy gets car sick and will throw up in the car. Amy is a quiet girl who does not bark much and she gets really excited to meet new dogs and people. Because of her nipping, Amy would do best in a home with older, dog savvy kids. She is also looking for a family who will commit to doing further training with her so that she can thrive in her new home. Amy is an active girl who is looking for an active family to go on lots of adventures with. 

From her foster: Amy is very active. She is great in her crate at night. Settles right down and goes to sleep. She plays hard and crashes hard. House training is going extremely well. She still likes to nip our hands and feet a lot though and can bark and try to challenge us when we tell her no. Treat training can be useful to distract her from bad behaviour and she sits and waits for her treats very patiently. She is a very smart girl and I believe she can be trained fairly quickly. Amy loves her walks, likes to pick up sticks, chase snowballs and the exercise helps tire her out and settle her down. She is pretty good on her leash but would need further training to walk right beside you and not to pull quite as much. She would probably be great in a family with another dog. She may be a bit nippy and excitable with young children. She is a sweet funny girl with a good temperament."

Think Amy sounds like the right dog for you? Complete an adoption application on our website; www.preciouspawsrescue.ca Her adoption fee is $650 and includes up to date vaccines, fecal test and deworming, wellness bloodwork and heartworm test, spay and microchip. All adopters receive 6 weeks of free pet insurance and local adopters will receive a 6 week obedience class FREE courtesy of Ruff Haus in Barrie (www.ruffhaus.ca)

animal.description:
Hey everyone! My name is Jackie I’m a 1 year old 35 pound hound mix. I’m also not spayed, whatever that means. What else? Oh, I came from West Virginia to Hixton WI where I’m currently being fostered. My foster mom says I’d do best in a home with another dog (I agree!) and I do very well with young children, my current foster family has a 3 year old that I’m buds with. I’m still unsure of cats, I tried smelling one once and it hit me on the nose. Also, I’ve been recently having a obsession with trying to run off (thankfully my foster family has a fenced yard) so my family will need to keep me tightly leashed or have a fenced yard until I trust people better and am trained. My foster mom wants to add that I’ve had a rough start and SO ready to be shown how good life can be, but with my rough start my new family will need to be patient with me and willing to work with me daily. My foster mom wants to tell my new family that my right back leg was hurt a long time ago but I get around just fine and seems to not bother me but I do limp sometimes and it looks scary. I’d love to meet you but don’t take offense if I act like I don’t. If your interested in coming to meet me and adding me to your family my adoption fee is $300 with a additional $100 for my spay deposit. Apply at www.lastpawrescue.org

501(c) approved Wisconsin Agriculture License # 285589-DS

animal.description:
We do not have a shelter - all our dogs are in private foster homes and we require an approved application to meet them.   Please visit our website at www.perfectpetsrescue.org for an application and more information.  Volunteers who answer email do not have information on specific dogs and will direct you to put in an application.  Thank you.
PLEASE read the requirements for Walter's new home before enquiring.

WALTER PAWIN is a cutie for sure!   Walter is a very mellow man looking for a special home that will understand his needs. His foster mom tells us:       Typically, Walter asks for lots of space to feel comfortable. Though you will know when he is ready for attention because he will sit at your feet, flop over, and ask for belly rubs! When he needs his space, he’s just as obvious about his wants. Walter would do best with a strong leader that is good at enforcing boundaries.   He is crate and house trained and walks well on a leash. He is dog friendly.  
No kids for Walter please.   Walter was not made available for adoption at animal control as he was not a happy camper and was very grumbly.  He needed rescue to get him out of there and we are glad we could help.   If you are interested in Walter, put in your application and we can put you in touch with his foster family to get more information on what kind of home would suit him best. 
The shelter aged Walter around 9 years old, but we think he may be younger,  and he weighs 16 lbs.
Walter has been vaccinated, dewormed, microchipped, heart worm tested negative and neutered.
We are asking for an adoption donation of $250 to help with the costs involved with caring for our rescue pets.
animal.name: Walter Pawin

animal.description:
Looking for a companion for walks and snuggles? Keeley is your girl. Since arriving at the farm, she has adjusted nicely and understands crate time and certainly playtime! Keeley is a 1-2-year-old lab mix weighing 45 lbs, a perfect size for either a home or apartment. She does well playing with other dogs and seeks out snuggles from any volunteer willing to accommodate her desire for ear rubs. Keeley is a lab mixed with other things wonderful and her personality shows it. She's looking for a forever family to make her own. Will it be yours? Don't delay - schedule time at SG to meet this girl!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

Around 2 years old, he is a solid boy that enjoys a good romp with his friends followed by a nap in the sun. He plays well with other dogs and seems to have some basic commands down pat. He's a smart boy that learns quickly, so a forever home that is filled with activity and togetherness will suit him to a tee! Solo, with other dogs, Othello will do fine. He did whisper during his bio interview that he would really like a comfy bed in his new home, preferably as close to his new family as possible. I don't even have that British reserve- I'm a friendly little girl! So, who can you resist a cute little package like me? Won't you be by James Bond and come get me so we can bond together?

Penny is a very sweet, social dog. She is around 1/2 years old and about 53lbs. She likes other dogs and kids too. This girl just like a ray of sunshine. Penny would make a great family dog.

IN NEED OF LOCAL FOSTER OR ADOPTER/ AVAILABLE FOR FOSTER TO ADOPT FOR LOCAL ADOPTERS

Meet Leona! More pictures and video to come!

Leona is 4 years old (approx. DOB tbd), female, 41 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed, and micro-chipped. Leona was found as a homeless stray in North Carolina. Leona is as sweet as can be! This gentle girl loves to play ball, gets along well with other dogs, and will even Sit for you for a treat!

What Leona wants the most is a loving forever family to call her own! Stay tuned for more information as Leona is a new rescue!

If you are interested in fostering or adopting Leona please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description:
Hello to you all,
I am Aria and I am a 6-8 month old Shepherd mix girl.  I have had my spay and my vaccinations.  And a microchip too.  

I enjoy playing with dogs and I would really love to find a home that has a dog to teach me stuff.  I love my Foster siblings,  we play and I am more brave when we go on walks together.  

While I am still a fun puppy,  I am housebroken and I don't destroy people belongings.  I like to carry your stuff around, but its done nicely ??

Do you have a yard?  I would love some space for potty and playing.   Maybe you like to go on drives?, cause I like to ride in a car.  And I even like to go to Doggie day camps too.  It's fun to have friends.  

Fill out the application to meet me, you will need to bring your dog too.  

Thanks a lot, love from Aria 

Aria is up to date on her vaccinations, spade and is currently being fostered in Flagstaff. Her adoption fee is $215

We are a small rescue/foster group without an animal shelter. If you are interested in meeting Aria, please fill out an online adoption application, located here: http://tubacityhumanesociety.org/tuba-city-humane-society-dogcat-online-adoption-application/ with more information about our adoption process here:
http://tubacityhumanesociety.org/adoptions/

Once we receive your application, which answers basic questions for us, we will have a conversation with you, before setting up a meeting. For more information, please contact Deb at dfranklin@tubacityhumanesociety.org or by phone at (928) 853-1046 (No calls after 7 p.m. please.)
